uawei Watch GT 3 in Kenya</h2><p>The Huawei Watch GT 3 price in Kenya is Ksh 28500. The Huawei Watch GT 3 is available in a variety of elegant styles',NULL,NULL,'Huawei-Watch-GT-3','Huawei-Watch-GT-3',32999,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(81,'Huawei Y9a','Huawei Y9a','Huawei-Y9a','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,14,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Huawei Y9a','<div class=\"col-item col-title\">\r\\n<div class=\"col-item col-title\">\r\\n<h3>HUAWEI AppGallery</h3>\r\\nHUAWEI AppGallery is Huawei\'s official app distribution platform to search, download, manage and share mobile apps. It continues to develop the global apps ecosystem to deliver secured, selected, and diversified experiences. Enjoy exclusive app content, local activities and special offers.\r\\n<h3 class=\"sub-tit\">8 GB+128 GB Large Storage</h3>\r\\n</div>\r\\n<div class=\"col-item col-text\">\r\\n\r\\nWith 8 GB RAM memory and 128 GB ROM memory, you can store all your important memories locally, keeping more photos, videos, files and messages.\r\\n\r\\n</div>\r\\n<h3>Charge Faster, Last Longer</h3>\r\\nHUAWEI Y9a is designed for quick charging speed and long battery life. With 40 W HUAWEI SuperCharge, you can charge up its battery efficiently, restoring nearly 70% power in 30 minutes<sup><a class=\"hw-notes\" data-index=\"3\">3</a></sup><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">. And its 4200 mAh large battery and AI power saving technology allow you to enjoy your journey without frequent </span><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"font-size: 16px;\">recharging</span>\r\\n\r\\n</div>',NULL,NULL,'Huawei-Y9a','Huawei-Y9a',35000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(82,'Infinix Hot 30','Infinix Hot 30','Infinix-Hot-30','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,6,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Infinix Hot 30','<h2>Infinix Hot 30 Specifications and features</h2>\r\\nThe Infinix Hot 30 price in Kenya is Kes 23,500. The device has a 6.78-inch IPS LCD 90Hz display that supports a screen resolution of 1080 x 2460 pixels. The Octa-core, Mediatek Helio G88 (12nm) processor powers the phone with Mali-G52 MC2 GPU. The phone has 8GB RAM and 256GB of internal storage; it runs on Android 13 OS, XOS 12.6 UI, and all this is powered by a 5,000 mAh battery with 33W fast charging. It also has a dual rear camera setup consisting of a 50MP (wide) primary camera and 0.08MP (Depth) Lens. At the front, use the 8MP for selfies\r\\n<h3>Physical Attributes</h3>\r\\nA large display dominates the front side of the Infinix Hot 30, with a punch hole to accommodate the front lens. The back and body frames are made of plastic. It weighs 196g and measures 168.7 x 76.6 x 8.4 mm. The measurements and weight are almost similar to the Hot 30i, which weighs 195g and measures 164.8 x 76.4 x 8.8 mm. The handset’s power button on the side also serves as the fingerprint sensor. A USB 2.0 Type C port enables charging and data transfer. The device comes in Racing Black, Surfing Green, Sonic White and Free Fire colour variants.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nThe Hot 30 features a cinematic, large 6.78-inch IPS LCD with high resolution that will give a better viewing experience, especially when playing games, watching movies or reading. It is immersive at 1080 x 2460 pixels (~396 ppi density). At 500 nits screen brightness and 90Hz refresh rate, Infinix Hot 30 gives an exceptional visual experience with sharp details outdoors, even in strong sunshine. It is far better than Infinix Hot 30i, which has a low 720p. Your screen will give you ready access to sharp images and videos wherever you are.\r\\n<h3>Processing Unit</h3>\r\\nInfinix Hot 30 boasts an Octa-core (2×2.0 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.8 GHz Cortex-A55) gaming engine with an advanced Mediatek Helio G88 (12nm) chipset and Mali-G52 MC2. They combine to form a formidable processing unit for gaming, multitasking, and internet browsing without lags and stuttering, even when used intensively.\r\\n\r\\nThe phone has 256GB 8GB RAM with additional memory support through microSDXC (dedicated slot). With such sufficiency in ROM and RAM, you are unlimited in terms of applications to download and use, storing multi-media, video games and large files, which otherwise slow down most other phones.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nInfinix Hot 30 is powered by a 5,000mAh battery. A fast, wired 33W charger recharges lithium battery. The battery will give you reliable service on day-to-night usage. You won’t necessarily need to spend your money on a power bank to supplement the power needs of the handset. The power marathon technology enables battery life extension. You can enjoy 2 hours of calling and up to 24 hours of standby time with 3% of the battery. Besides, 33w fast charging enables 1-55% recharge in 30 minutes.\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3383\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3383\" aria-labelledby=\"tablepress-3383-name\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Infinix</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Infinix Hot 30</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-4\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Announced</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>March, 2023</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-5\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Released</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>March, 2023</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-6\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Operating System</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Android 13, XOS 12.6</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-7\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Chipset</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Mediatek Helio G88 (12nm)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-8\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>CPU Speed</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Octa-core (2×2.0 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.8 GHz Cortex-A55)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr