\\n<div>Fast Charging 18W\r\\nReverse charging 5W</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-32\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Colors</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Racing Black, Luna Blue, Aurora Green, Fantasy Purple</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Infinix-Hot-30-Play','Infinix-Hot-30-Play',20000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(84,'Infinix Hot 30i','Infinix Hot 30i','Infinix-Hot-30i','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,6,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Infinix Hot 30i','<h2>Infinix Hot 30i Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<table>\r\\n<tbody>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Brand</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Infinix</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Model</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Hot 30i, X669</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Price</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Kes 16,300</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Release Date</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">27 March 2023</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Dimensions</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Weight: 195g, Size: 164.8 x 76.4 x 8.8 mm</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Display</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Size: 6.6 inches, Type: IPS LCD, Resolution: 720x1612p (~267ppi), Refresh rate: 90Hz</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Camera Set up</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Dual primary camera 13MP, Selfie Camera: 8MP</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Processing Unit</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Chipset: Unisoc 7606 12nm, CPU:2x Cortex-A75 and 6x Cortex-A55 cores, GPU: Mali-G57 MP1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Operating System</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Android 12</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Memory Space</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">4GB RAM (4GB) expandable RAM) to 8GB, 128GB inbuilt memory space, Supports additional memory with a dedicated slot</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Sensors</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Side-mounted fingerprint scanner, Acceleration, Rotation, Proximity, and Compass</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Battery</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">5,000mAh with 18W wired fast charger</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>Color</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Diamond White, Glacier Blue, Mirror Black</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>\r\\n<h3>Hot 30i Physical Attributes</h3>\r\\nA large water-drop glass display dominates the front side of the Infinix Hot 30i. The back and body frames are made of plastic. It weighs 195g and measures 164.8 x 76.4 x 8.8 mm. the power button on the side of the handset also serves as the fingerprint sensor. A USB 2.0 Type C port enables charging and data transfer. The device comes in Diamond White, Glacier Blue, and Mirror Black color variants.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nThe Hot 30i features a cinematic, 6.6-inch IPS LCD with high resolution that will give a better viewing experience, especially when playing games, watching movies or reading. At 720 x 1612 pixels, it is not one of the best but still functional especially considering the handset is an entry-level smartphone. At 500 nits screen brightness and 90Hz refresh rate, Infinix Hot 30i given es exceptional visual experience with sharp details outdoors even in strong sunshine. Your screen will give you ready access to sharp images and videos wherever you are.\r\\n<h3>Processing Unit</h3>\r\\nInfinix Hot 30i boasts an Octa-core gaming engine with a 1a 2nm advanced production processor that will easily handle your daily needs t has up to 8GB expansion, with RAM extension technology that doubles the original 4GB RAM to an incredible. This makes your phone faster in processing and allows for more apps to run simultaneously.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nInfinix Hot 30i is powered by a 5,000mAh battery. A fast, wired 18W charger recharges lithium battery. The battery will give you reliable service on day-to-night usage. You won’t necessarily need to spend your money on a power bank to supplement the power needs of the handset. The power marathon technology enables battery life extension. You can enjoy 2 hours of calling and up to 24 hours of standby time with 3% of the battery.',NULL,NULL,'Infinix-Hot-30i','Infinix-Hot-30i',20000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(85,'Infinix Hot 40 Pro','Infinix Hot 40 Pro','Infinix-Hot-40-Pro','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,6,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Infinix Hot 40 Pro','<h2>Infinix Hot 40 Pro Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\nInfinix Hot 40 Pro 4G price in Kenya is 30,000 shillings. The device has a 6.78-inch IPS LCD 90Hz display that supports a screen resolution of 1080 x 2460 pixels (~396 ppi density). An Octa-core Mediatek Helio G99 (6nm) processor powers the phone with Mali-G57 MC2 GPU for a seamless gaming experience. The phone has 128GB, 8GB RAM, and 256GB, 8GB RAM of internal storage, runs on Android 13 and XOS 13.5, and is powered by a 5,000 mAh battery with 33W wired, 20-75% in 35 min fast charging unit. It also features a triple rear camera setup consisting of a 108MP + 2MP +0.08MP primary camera and a 32MP (wide) selfie camera. The Infinix Hot 40 Pro 4G comes in Palm Blue, Horizon Gold, Starlit Black, Starfall Green, and Free Fire color variants.\r\\n<h3>Product Description</h3>\r\\n<h4>Physical Attributes</h4>\r\\nA large center-notched glass display dominates the front side of the Infinix Hot 40 Pro 4G. The back and body frames are made of plastic. It weighs 199g and measures 168.6 x 76.6 x 8.3 mm (6.64 x 3.02 x 0.33 in), which are dimensions almost similar to Hot 40i. The handset’s power button on the side also serves as the fingerprint sensor. A USB 2.0 Type C port enables charging and data transfer. The device comes in Palm Blue, Horizon Gold, Starlit Black, Starfall Green, and Free Fire color variants. Notably, the handset has a side-mounted fingerprint scanner, supports Dual SIM Cards input, and is not waterproof.\r\\n<h4>Display</h4>\r\\nThe Hot 40 Pro 4G features a high-quality, 6.78-inch IPS LCD that will give you a good viewing experience, especially when playing games, watching movies, or reading. It is one of the best smartphones for that price range with 1080 x 2460 pixels (~396 ppi density) resolution, thus value for money. At 500 nits (peak) screen brightness and 120Hz refresh rate, Infinix Hot 40 Pro gives an exceptional visual experience with sharp details outdoors, even in strong sunshine. Your screen will give you ready access to sharp images and videos wherever you are.\r\\n<h5 class=\"text title\"><span class=\"text-blue-green-white text-bold\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">8X Precise </span>Touching Sampling</h5>\r\\n<div class=\"text body\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Experience lightning-fast gaming with Infinix’ s 1200Hz instantaneous touch sampling rate, 8x more precise than standard screens. Swiftly capturing touches and delivering instant feedback keeps you ahead in gaming’s critical moments.</div>\r\\n<h5><span class=\"text title\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Magic Ring</span></h5>\r\\n<span class=\"text desc\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Discover a seamless experience like never before with our Magic Ring. Effortlessly stay<br class=\"content-pc\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\" />informed about face unlock, charging progress, and voice calls. It immerses you in a world<br class=\"content-pc\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\" />of captivating experiences, keeping you in the spotlight wherever you go.</span>\r\\n<h4>Processing Unit</h4>\r\\nInfinix Hot 40 Pro 4G boasts an Octa-core gaming engine with an advanced <a href=\"https://www.mediatek.com/products/smartphones-2/mediatek-helio-g99\">Mediatek Helio G99 (6nm)</a> processor that will easily handle your daily needs. It has 128GB 8GB RAM / 256GB 8GB RAM, besides a dedicated microSDXC slot, making it great for gaming and intensive use without running out of space or slowing down on processing speed.\r\\n<h5>Mega RAM</h5>\r\\nenjoy up to 16GB RAM, empowering you to 18 Apps Switching at will. Infinix RAM extension technology doubles the original 8GB RAM to an amazing 16GB. Booting faster and allowing more<br data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\" />apps to run at the same time.\r\\n<h5>Boosted Gaming Experience</h5>\r\\n<div class=\"text body\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">The new-Gen Gaming Engine undoubtedly changes the gaming experience. Experience our self-developed XBOOST gaming engine, frame-by-frame calibrated for seamless performance. During gameplay, swipe left to access a tactical panel, offering one-click optimization for enhanced stability experience.</div>\r\\n<div data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">\r\\n<h5 class=\"text title text-bold\">Folax</h5>\r\\n<div class=\"text subtitle\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Infinix Hot 40 Pro comes with a better, more empathetic voice assistant.  Your multilingual Folax assistant is always online, even when you are not connected to the internet. Wake Folax to help you make calls, take photos, play music, set alarms.</div>\r\\n</div>\r\\n<h4>Hot 40 Pro Camera Set up</h4>\r\\n<div data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">\r\\n<h5 class=\"text title\">108MP Triple AI Camera</h5>\r\\n<div class=\"text subtitle\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Stay Amazing Anytime, Anywhere. <span class=\"content-pc\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Paired with the HM6 sensor, our 108 MP high-res lens captures details with 0.64-micron pixels, enabling you to easily shape and remix your pictures into stunning masterpieces. Regardless of the cropping, everything captures by the lens remains crystal clear.</span></div>\r\\n<h6>Zooming</h6>\r\\n<div data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Zoom in even further than before with the 2MP Macro lens, allowing you to shoot stunning extreme close ups of your subjects.</div>\r\\n<h5>Crystal Clear Selfies</h5>\r\\n<div data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Experience the flagship front camera for clear selfies, even in low light with the front flash. Capture group photos easily with an intelligent 90° wide-angle lens, including you and friends seamlessly in the frame.</div>\r\\n</div>\r\\n<h4>Connectivity and Communication Capabilities</h4>\r\\n<h5>GSM Connectivity</h5>\r\\nThe handset is 4G enabled and runs on GSM / HSPA / LTE network technology and HSPA, LTE. Uploading and downloading speeds are commendable and will get the job done, but not as efficiently as fast as experienced on 5G.\r\\n<h6 class=\"text title text-bold\">First-in-Class Metamaterial Antenna</h6>\r\\n<div class=\"text subtitle\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Infinix Hot 40 Pro comes packaged for Future High-Speed Network, with the the groundbreaking Metamaterial Antenna, featuring a three times larger antenna area. This results in enhanced efficiency, broader bandwidth, and faster, reliable signal performance.</div>\r\\n<h5>Internet and Other forms of connectivity</h5>\r\\n<div data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">Use fast and safe internet connectivity using the installed Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band on the Infinix Hot 40 Pro 4G.</div>\r\\nBluetooth pairing is equally smooth and efficient, with the installed version supporting seamless pairing with your smart devices (smartwatch, TV, Headphones).\r\\n\r\\nThe Infinix device supports GPS, NFC, and FM Radio and comes installed with a 3.5mm jack port. If you love to plug in your headphones and listen to your favorite FM Radio shows or MP3 music hits, you will love the experience on the Hot 40 Pro.\r\\n<h5>Gyroscope</h5>\r\\n<div class=\"text body\" data-v-70d3f6c4=\"\">The Gyroscope sensor enhances 3D spatial detection. Calibration ensures unmatched accuracy, enabling precise in-game hand tracking.</div>\r\\n<h4>Battery</h4>\r\\nInfinix Hot 40 Pro 4G is powered by a 5,000mAh battery. A fast, wired 33W charger recharges lithium batteries (20-75% in 35 minutes). The battery will give you reliable service on day-to-night usage. You won’t necessarily need to spend your money on a power bank to supplement the power needs of the handset. A 5000mAh battery combined with the exclusive Power Marathon solution can support incredible all-day standby time or up to 2 hours of calling even when the power is as low as 5%.\r\\n<h5>Fast Charging</h5>\r\\n33W FastCharge technology delivers rapid full charging for your enjoyment while ensuring user safety and extending battery life with real-time temperature monitoring. Even after 4 years, just one charge a day is all you need.\r\\n<h5>Reverse Charging</h5>\r\\nBesides the 33W fast charging, the handset supports reverse-wired charging. Thus, it can be used as a power bank to charge your other smartphone, Bluetooth headphones, or smartwatch on the go if you are away from a power source and need to use these devices.',NULL,NULL,'Infinix-Hot-40-Pro','Infinix-Hot-40-Pro',28999,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(86,'Infinix Hot 40i','Infinix Hot 40i','Infinix-Hot-40i','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,6,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Infinix Hot 40i','<h2 class=\"product_title entry-title\">Infinix Hot 40i Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\nInfinix Hot 40i price in Kenya is 17,500 shillings. Hot 40i has a 6.56-inch IPS LCD 90Hz display that supports a screen resolution of 720 x 1612 pixels. The Unisoc T606 processor powers the phone with Mali-G57 MP1 GPU. It boasts of an impressive 128GB, 4GB RAM, 256GB 8GB RAM of internal storage, runs on Android 13 and XOS 13, and is powered by a 5,000 mAh battery with 18W fast charging. Moreover, it has a dual rear camera setup with a 50MP(wide) primary camera, 0.08MP (Auxiliary Lens), and a 32 MP, f/2.2, (wide) selfie camera. The Infinix Hot 40i comes in Starlit Black, Palm Blue, Horizon Gold, and Starfall Green\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<h3>Product Description</h3>\r\\n<h4>Physical Attributes</h4>\r\\nA large center-notched glass display dominates the front side of the Infinix Hot 40i. The back and body frames are made of plastic. It weighs 190g and measures 163.6 x 75.6 x 8.3 mm, making it slimmer than the Hot 30i. The handset’s power button on the side also serves as the fingerprint sensor. A USB 2.0 Type C port enables charging and data transfer. The device comes in Starlit Black, Palm Blue, Horizon Gold, and Starfall Green color variants. Notably, the handset has a side-mounted fingerprint scanner, supports Dual SIMs, and is not waterproof.\r\\n<h4>Display</h4>\r\\nThe Hot 40i features a high-quality, 6.56-inch IPS LCD that will give you a good viewing experience, especially when playing games, watching movies, or reading. At 720 x 1612 pixels, it is not one of the best but still functional, especially considering the handset is an entry-level smartphone. With 480 nits (peak) screen brightness and 90Hz refresh rate, Infinix Hot 40i gives an exceptional visual experience with sharp details outdoors, even in strong sunshine. Your screen will give you ready access to sharp images and videos wherever you are.\r\\n<h4>Processing Unit</h4>\r\\nInfinix Hot 40i boasts an Octa-core gaming engine with an advanced <a href=\"https://nanoreview.net/en/soc/unisoc-t606\">Unisoc T606 (12 nm)</a> processor that will easily handle your daily needs. It has 128GB, 4GB RAM, 256GB, and 8GB RAM, besides a dedicated microSDXC slot, making it great for gaming and intensive use without running out of space or slowing down on processing speed.\r\\n<h4>Connectivity and Communication Capabilities</h4>\r\\nThe handset is 4G enabled and runs on GSM / HSPA / LTE  network technology and HSPA, LTE. Uploading and downloading speeds are commendable and will get the job done, but not as efficiently as fast as experienced on 5G.\r\\n\r\\nUse fast and safe internet connectivity using the installed Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band on the Infinix Hot 40i.\r\\n\r\\nBluetooth pairing is equally smooth and efficient, with the installed version supporting seamless pairing with your smart devices (smartwatch, TV, Headphones).\r\\n\r\\nThe Infinix device supports GPS, NFC, and FM Radio and comes installed with a 3.5mm jack port. If you love to plug in your headphones and listen to your favorite FM Radio shows or mp3 music hits, you will love the experience on the Hot 40i.\r\\n<h4>Battery</h4>\r\\nInfinix Hot 40i is powered by a 5,000mAh battery. A fast, wired 18W charger recharges lithium battery. The battery will give you reliable service on day-to-night usage. You won’t necessarily need to spend your money on a power bank to supplement the power needs of the handset. The power marathon technology enables battery life extension. You can enjoy 2 hours of calling and up to 24 hours of standby time with 3% of the battery.\r\\n\r\\nBesides the 18W fast charging, the handset supports reverse-wired charging. Thus, it can be used as a power bank to charge your other smartphone, Bluetooth headphones, or smartwatch on the go if you are away from a power source and need to use these devices.',NULL,NULL,'Infinix-Hot-40i','Infinix-Hot-40i',28999,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(87,'Infinix Hot 40i - 128GB','Infinix Hot 40i - 128GB','Infinix-Hot-40i-128GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,6,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Infinix Hot 40i - 128GB','Infinix Hot 40i - 256GB',NULL,NULL,'Infinix-Hot-40i-128GB','Infinix-Hot-40i-128GB',22000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(88,'Infinix Hot 40i - 256GB','Infinix Hot 40i - 256GB','Infinix-Hot-40i-256GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,6,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Infinix Hot 40i - 256GB','Infinix Hot 40i - 256GB',NULL,NULL,'Infinix-Hot-40i-256GB','Infinix-Hot-40i-256GB',24500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(89,'Infinix Note 30','Infinix Note 30','Infinix-Note-30','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,6,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Infinix Note 30','<h2>Infinix Note 30 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\nThe Infinix Note 30 price in Kenya is Ksh 26,000 at ROPEM PHONES. The Infinix Note 30 is powered by the Mediatek Helio G85 (12nm) processor with Mali-G52 MC2 GPU all this is powered by a 5,000 mAh battery with 45W All-Round FastCharge. The phone comes in 8 GB RAM 256GB of internal storage which is expandable u