that shows status updates and charging information.\r\\n<h4>Processor</h4>\r\\nThe Infinix Smart 8 is powered by the <a href=\"https://nanoreview.net/en/soc/unisoc-t606\">Unisoc T606</a> chipset, a 12 nm octa-core processor with two Cortex-A75 cores and six Cortex-A55 cores. It has a Mali-G57 MP1 GPU for graphics. The processing power is sufficient for multitasking and low-setting gaming.\r\\n<h4>Memory</h4>\r\\nInfinix Smart 8 has 3GB of RAM and 64GB/128GB of internal storage, which can be expanded with a microSD card. It also has Virtual RAM, which allows the phone to use 3GB of extra memory from the storage. Thus, you have sufficient storage for your videos, pictures, and other files that you deem essential and always want to be with you.\r\\n<h4>Camera Setup</h4>\r\\nIt has a dual rear camera setup consisting of a 13 MP primary camera with autofocus and a 0.3 MP depth sensor. It also has a dual-LED flash, HDR, and panorama modes. The front camera is an 8 MP shooter with an LED flash.\r\\n<h4>Software</h4>\r\\nInfinix Smart 8 runs on Android 13, with Infinix’s custom XOS 13 skin on top. The XOS 13 offers Smart Panel, Game Mode, Social Turbo, and Xhide features.\r\\n<h4>Battery</h4>\r\\nIt has a 5,000mAh battery, which supports 10W fast charging. The battery lasts up to 24 hours of talk time, 40 hours of music playback, or 15 hours of video playback.\r\\n<h4>Other features</h4>\r\\nThe device has a fingerprint scanner, a 3.5 mm headphone jack, a Micro-USB port, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, GPS, and FM radio. It also supports dual SIM cards and 4G LTE networks.',NULL,NULL,'Infinix-Smart-8','Infinix-Smart-8',16000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(96,'Infinix Zero 30 5G','Infinix Zero 30 5G','Infinix-Zero-30-5G','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,6,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Infinix Zero 30 5G','<h2>Infinix Zero 30 5G</h2>\r\\nThe Infinix Zero 30 5G features a 6.78-inch AMOLED display with a 144Hz refresh rate. Mediatek Dimensity 8020 (6 nm) SoC powers the phone with up to 12GB of RAM and 256GB of internal storage. It packs a 5,000mAh battery with support for 68W fast charging technology. You have run on XOS 13.1 UI and Android’s latest 13 OS for applications and customization. The smartphone sports a single 50MP selfie snapper and a triple camera system at the rear. The rear setup has a 108MP primary lens, a 13MP secondary lens, and a 2MP sensor with an LED flash.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<h3>Display and Design</h3>\r\\nIt is a slim, sleek phone that is featherlight. Infinix Zero 30 5G is as elegant as you would ever want a smartphone to be, with its body consisting of a Glass front (Gorilla Glass 5), glass back (Gorilla Glass 5) or eco-leather back, plastic frame. The body design and build ooze class, elegance and demand for attention. Furthermore, its aesthetics make it stand out, adding to it the delicacy, intricateness in design and deliberate effort to connect with your innermost fantasies.\r\\n\r\\nMeasuring 164.5 x 75 x 7.9 mm and weighing 185g, you will certainly not miss its 7.9mm thickness, which is ‘paper thin’ going by the standards of smartphones. Indeed, it will fit perfectly in your pocket as you go with your business. Pulling it out to check notifications and maybe pick/make a call is hustle-free, considering its fitting size and lightweight at 185g.\r\\n\r\\nMoreover, the phone is IP53 rated (dust and splash-resistant) and has Corning Gorilla Glass 5. These features are great for the Infinix Zero 30, whilst they give you peace of mind when caught out in a sudden storm or the phone falls accidentally. Available in Rome Green, Golden Hour, and Fantasy Purple, the phone is a beauty to behold, with the aesthetics pre-emptive of more to come once the device is turned on.\r\\n<h4>Display</h4>\r\\nInfinix Zero 30  features an impressively assembled, large and illuminative 6.78-inch AMOLED, AMOLED, 1B colours, 144Hz, 950 nits (peak) display. With a 90% screen-to-body ratio and 1080 x 2400 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~388 ppi density) resolution, Infinix outdid themselves with their new flagship phone. The thin bezels on the button-hole 950 nits peak brightness AMOLED display create some of the best cinematic, immersive and unforgettable experiences you can ever have on a smartphone. You will undoubtedly lose yourself while streaming videos and engaging your nemesis in the select video games of your picking. Additionally, the Corning Gorilla Glass on the Infinix Zero 30 5G indicatively shows Infinix have invested wholesomely in creating the best experiences for their users and protecting the impressive AMOLED display installed using the best protector available on the mobile market.\r\\n<h3>The camera setup on the Infinix Zero 30 5G</h3>\r\\nCapture captivating, high-quality pictures and videos with the impressive camera set-up on the Infinix Zero 30.\r\\n<h4>Selfies</h4>\r\\nUndeniably, a single, 50 MP, f/2.5, (wide)，1/2.76″, PDAF with LED flash is a statement of intent. If you are a selfie lover, you will be a dear, sweet friend and companion in the Infinix phone. Not only does it shoot unique, high quality and excellent selfies, but it equally records highly coveted 4K and 1080p videos. It would be best if you never missed a moment at work, at a party or out in the wild to snap away some awesome selfies or record videos with the impressive front-facing 50MP (wide) lens.\r\\n<h4>Infinix Zero 30 main Camera</h4>\r\\nIt features a triple-camera set-up. Impressively assembled, the integrated camera system at the phone’s rear end consists of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>108 MP, f/1.7, (wide), 1/1.67″, PDAF, OIS</li>\r\\n 	<li>13 MP, f/2.2, 120˚ (ultrawide)</li>\r\\n 	<li>2 MP, f/2.4</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThese cameras combine to capture some of the best high-definition pictures ever on Infinix smartphones. The AI-enhanced snap photos are not only of high quality but comparatively improved when competing with the most advanced 50MP shots. Furthermore, the integrated main camera system features LED flash, HDR, and panorama, giving you options when seeking the best images from different perspectives. Moreover, Zero 30 main camera records 1080p and 4K videos, thereby joining the exclusive club of mid-range smartphones capable of recording up to 4K videos.\r\\n\r\\nAssuredly, you will have a great time using the smartphone as you turn your passion for photography and videography to a different level with such a high-quality camera in your hands, unlimited internal memory and a powerful processor that ensures peak performance whenever and wherever you are.\r\\n<h3>Infinix Zero 30 Performance</h3>\r\\n<h4>Operating System</h4>\r\\nThe mid-range phone holds punch when it comes to performance. Infinix installed the latest Android 13 on their Zero 30 model, along with their XOS 13 UI. Combined, the OS and UI work in unison to maximise your experience as you immerse yourself into the downloaded and default applications and social media interactions and customise the phone’s appearance to suit your mood, personality and motivations.\r\\n<h4>Processor</h4>\r\\nInfinix Zero 30 possesses a reliable and decent processor. The Octa-core, Mediatek Dimensity 8020 (6 nm) chipset integrated with Mali-G77 MC9 ensures your phone operations run smoothly. Whether multi-tasking across several applications simultaneously, playing games, streaming videos or browsing through heavy files, the phones keep up with the pace. Lags, stuttering and overheating should be the least of your worries as you maximise your time on productivity and entertainment.\r\\n<h4>Memory</h4>\r\\nThe phone Infinix Zero 30 5G does not come with a MicroSD slot for additional memory. Nevertheless, it packs an impressive internal memory and RAM. The model options comprise 256GB internal memory, 8GB RAM or 256GB 12GB RAM. Considerably, 8GB/12GB are a massive call for uncompromised performance with the phone, backing up the processor and undeniable raw processing power on the Zero 30. You are undoubtedly unlimited in space, with up to 256G available for indulgence.\r\\n<h3>Connectivity</h3>\r\\nThis is a <a href=\"https://www.safaricom.co.ke/media-center-landing/frequently-asked-questions/5g\">5G network-enabled</a> smartphone, capable of fast uploading and downloading speeds.\r\\n\r\\nTo improve your connectivity and communications, the device features:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>First, A USB Type-C 2.0, OTG for wired data transfer to other devices</li>\r\\n 	<li>Secondly, WLAN via Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/6, dual-band for best and fast, buffering-less internet connectivity</li>\r\\n 	<li>Thirdly, Bluetooth connectivity to pair your smart devices and transfer data.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Fourthly, several sensors, including a fingerprint (under display, optical) sensor, accelerometer, gyro, proximity, and compass sensor</li>\r\\n 	<li>NFC</li>\r\\n 	<li>Furthermore, the dual speakers improve audibility and increase sound output quality.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nUnfortunately, the phone has no 3.5mm jack. It would be best to rely on Bluetooth connectivity or an adapter on a USB Type C port to access and use FM Radio or your addictive headsets.\r\\n<h3>Battery and Recharging</h3>\r\\nInfinix Zero 30 5G is a big phone with an unreserved hunger for power to run operations, illuminate the 6.78-inch display and keep your appetite for an uncompromised immersive experience. As you immerse yourself in endless games, social media interactions and video streaming, undoubtedly, the 5,000mAh battery keeps up with power consumption demands. Intelligent power management by the phone’s processor ensures power is optimally used wherever the phone is powered on and automatically minimized power use once the phone goes idle. When power is needed, plug it into the wall and quickly get the 68W wired adapter recharging the battery. It charges 1-80% of the battery in 30 minutes, which is impressive.',NULL,NULL,'Infinix-Zero-30-5G','Infinix-Zero-30-5G',56000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(97,'Itel A04','Itel A04','Itel-A04','uploads/cust