UV rays from the sun, making it a great phone to behold as you work and play out in the sun due to the Photochromatic feature on the back and body frame of the phone.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nThe phone has a massive 90Hz, 6.6-inch IPS LCD HD+ screen that is fast and fluid. The display boasts a 1612 x 720p resolution, a 90 Hz refresh rate, and a touch sampling rate of 180 Hz. Good display for a budget phone, making it comfortable when browsing the internet, searching through your gallery and watching movies.\r\\n<h3>Camera Set Up</h3>\r\\nCapture modest selfies with the front-facing 8MP AI camera. The camera automatically adjusts brightness, allowing you to shine with the best selfie shots.\r\\n\r\\nThe primary camera is a 50MP Ultra camera that ensures no dull moment as you work and have fun.  The high-definition photo system with F1.6 Aperture gives you some of the best shots ever taken on an Itel phone, along with 1080p video recordings.\r\\n<h3>Itel S23 Performance</h3>\r\\nThe phone features 8GB + 8GB RAM and 128GB internal memory. The massive phone storage space makes it fast, accommodating large files and fun to use without the usual limitations on most other budget phones.\r\\n\r\\nThe additional memory via the MicroSD can be extended to 1TB. It relies on Android 12 OS for running applications in the background. Powering the phone system is an Octa-core, UNISOC T606 processor crucial for multitasking and playing basic games.\r\\n<h3>Power Charging System</h3>\r\\nItel S23 4G is powered by a massive 5,000mAh battery, which helps the phone run for 1-2 days before recharge, depending on usage. Once fully charged, it will give hours on YouTube, Calls, Internet browsing and Game Playing. The phone allows you 46 days of standby time and 31 hours Talktime.\r\\n\r\\nPhone Security includes a Front Face Camera ID Unlock feature and a side-mounted fingerprint scanner. These features help limit unauthorised access to your phone and use of your airtime, data bundles or even make calls to family and friends. To recharge, make use of the wired 10W fast recharging unit.',NULL,NULL,'Itel-S23','Itel-S23',16000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(110,'Itel S23+','Itel S23+','Itel-S23+','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,7,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Itel S23+','<h2>Itel S23+ in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Design</h3>\r\\nItel S23+  handset is sleek and slim, undisputedly beautiful to own and hold. A dual-curved design places perfect curves and intricate artwork in your hands. The advanced Iridescent thick-plating technique makes the s23+ so colourful and perfectly creates the beauty of the lake and mountain. With vibrant and fantasy colours in your hand, you easily become the crowd’s focus. Itel s23+ comes in two distinctive colours: Black and cyan.\r\\n\r\\nIts 7.9 mm thickness makes it one of the slimmest handsets ever released by Itel, besides it rivalling other brands’ thinnest handsets, such as Xiaomi. Equally, the phone is featherlight at 178g, which could be attributed to its build: a glass front, plastic frame, and plastic back.\r\\n<h3>Itel S23+ Display</h3>\r\\nExperience the incredible and immersive visuals on the flagship curved screen, which is 6.78 inches in size and boasts a wide-color gamut of 99% DCI-P3, a resolution of FHD+, and super narrow borders. Drive into immersive visuals with the impressive, curved AMOLED display boasts of an impressive 500 nits brightness and 1080 x 2400 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~388 ppi density). Gaming and watching videos will be a new experience on your Itel S23+.\r\\n\r\\nItel s23+ screen dazzles with remarkable 500-nit brightness, delivering sharp visuals and unbeatable viewing comfort, even under the brightest sunlight.\r\\n\r\\nNotably, the display has a 240Hz in-display fingerprint sensor that is conveniently located to enable you to easily lock/unlock your smartphone and prevent unauthorized access to your device, especially when you are charging it or not having the phone with you all the time.\r\\n<h3>Camera Set up</h3>\r\\nThe latest Itel sensational handset features an impressive set of cameras.\r\\n<h5>Selfies</h5>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Camera: single 32 MP, f/2.0 lens</li>\r\\n 	<li>Video recording capabilities: 1080p@30fps</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h5>Main Camera</h5>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>50 MP, f/1.6, (wide), AF</li>\r\\n 	<li>08 MP supporting lens</li>\r\\n 	<li>Video recording capabilities: 1080p@30fps</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Processor</h3>\r\\nItel s23+ is powered by a robust and reliable octa-core Unisoc Tiger T616 (12 nm) processor. The processor produces sufficient power to enable smooth operations in the background, multi-tasking with multiple applications running . Mali-G57 MP1 GPU, integrated into the Unisoc Tiger T616 (12 nm) chip, helps ensure mid-level set games are as enjoyable as possible with minimal heating up and lagging due to overloading.\r\\n<h3>Itel S23+ Operating System</h3>\r\\nIt runs on the latest Android 13, itel OS 13. The all-new itel OS 13 is the smoothest to date on Itel smartphones. It consists of an advanced and fluid design, a sleek card-based layout, and smooth, intelligent animation. These include a more intuitive Smart AOD and other cool features to lock in this seamless experience.\r\\n<h3>Battery and Power Management</h3>\r\\nItel s23+ is powered by a high capacity, Li-Po 5,000 mAh, non-removable battery. With the impressive 5,000mAh large battery and AI Power Master intelligent battery management, the handset offers long-lasting battery life, keeping you worry-free. You can freely take photos, watch your favourite shows, or indulge in various games without worrying about the battery running out.\r\\n\r\\n18W Type-C Fast Charge lets you keep up with the power demands from operating the handsets as you immerse yourself in endless gaming and watching videos on the bright, high-resolution display. Charge in a flash with the 18W fast charging unit. Combined with a safer Type-C connection and super-fast charging method, your device is fully charged within 2 hours of getting plugged into a power source.',NULL,NULL,'Itel-S23+','Itel-S23+',25000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(111,'Lightning to USB Cable (1 m)','Lightning to USB Cable (1 m)','Lightning-to-USB-Cable-(1-m)','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,13,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Lightning to USB Cable (1 m)','<div class=\"electro-description clearfix\"><h2 id=\"title\" class=\"a-size-large a-spacing-none\">Lightning to USB Cable (1 m)</h2><p>Lightning to USB Cable price in Kenya is Ksh 2500. The Apple Lightning to USB-C charging cable allows you to connect any device with a lightning connection to a USB-C enabled device. Connect your iPhone',NULL,NULL,'Lightning-to-USB-Cable-(1-m)','Lightning-to-USB-Cable-(1-m)',2200,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(112,'Nokia C1 2nd Edition','Nokia C1 2nd Edition','Nokia-C1-2nd-Edition','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,8,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Nokia C1 2nd Edition','<h3>Nokia C1 2nd Edition specs and price in Kenya</h3>\r\\n<h3>Display and Camera</h3>\r\\nYes, there are bezels here on this 2021 smartphone. Bummer! They are both on the top and at the bottom. Its display on the other hand is a 5.45 inches TFT capacitive touchscreen with a 480 x 960 pixels resolution. The Nokia C1 2nd Edition display has an 18:9 ratio and 197 PPI density. By the way, the video recording here is 720p@30fps as one would expect.\r\\n\r\\n<iframe title=\"Nokia C1 2nd Edition - Make every moment count\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/eCRtrwgl7h0?feature=oembed&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https://www.phoneplacekenya.com\" width=\"1170\" height=\"658\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe>\r\\n\r\\nI want to think that anyone who wishes to buy Nokia C1 2nd Edition will be asking too much if s/he  asked for more than this phone has to offer. Even for its display even for its cameras. Here is a 5 MP, f/2.4, AF main camera, and a bright 5 MP front-facing camera. I say bright because it is accompanied by an LED flash.\r\\n<h3>Android 11 (Go edition)</h3>\r\\nFrom features that make the world more inclusive to tools that change lives, Android (Go edition) is a platform with a major impact. The lens in Google Go reads written language out loud, helping more people understand the world around them. On Android (Go edition), Google apps are built from the ground up—so apps use less space, save data and stay loaded with power. They are giving users new tools to capture the perfect shot. Or listen to a webpage. While keeping everything faster, more helpful, and easier to use – from the <a href=\"https://www.android.com/versions/go-edition/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">source</a> Google.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nNokia has a splendid reputation with battery lives. On Nokia C1 2nd Edition is a removable (yes removable) Li-Ion 2500 mAh battery. We rarely see removable batteries these days, but for those who wish to have a phone with it, try Nokia C1. Get 2-3 days of usage with this battery capacity – see also the Nokia C1 phone.\r\\n<table class=\"mdl-data-table mdl-js-data-table\" data-upgraded=\",MaterialDataTable\">\r\\n<tbody>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"></td>\r\\n<td></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Display</strong></td>\r\\n<td>5.45 inches, IPS LCD</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Processor</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Unisoc SC7731e</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Sim Card</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Dual SIM</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Connectivity</strong></td>\r\\n<td>4G</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>OS</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Android 11 (Go edition)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>RAM</strong></td>\r\\n<td>1 GB</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Storage</strong></td>\r\\n<td>16 GB</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Battery</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Li-Ion 2500 mAh</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Camera</strong></td>\r\\n<td>5 MP</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Selfie</strong></td>\r\\n<td>5 MP</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Nokia-C1-2nd-Edition','Nokia-C1-2nd-Edition',13500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(113,'Nokia C12','Nokia C12','Nokia-C12','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,8,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Nokia C12','<h2>Nokia C12 Pro Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Build and Design</h3>\r\\nNokia C21 is a Dual SIM smartphone measuring 160.6 x 74.3 x 8.8 mm. it weighs 177g. it is made of a Glass front, plastic back, and plastic frame. Nokia C12 is made for modern times – and that includes the design. With its sculpted rear with a metallic finish and a 3D pattern for a better grip, it boasts a look that’s modern today and timeless tomorrow. And being a Nokia smartphone, it’s been tested over and over again and comes with better durability against dust, moisture and accidental drops.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nVideos and apps look great on the 6.3” HD+ IPS LCD with a selfie notch that maximizes screen space. All of this on a phone that’s comfortable to hold in one hand. The resolution is 720 x 1600 pixels (~278 ppi density). The display comes protected by Scratch-resistant glass.\r\\n<h3>Nokia C12 Camera set up.</h3>\r\\nNokia C12 combines cameras with powerful imaging software for Night and Portrait modes (both front and rear cameras). Capture selfies with the 5MP, alongside 720p videos. At the back, take shots with the 8MP AF camera. The main camera comes along with LED flash and HDR. You can capture 720P videos using the 8MP camera.\r\\n<h3>Processor and Space</h3>\r\\nNokia C12 comes with an up-to-date Android 12 (Go edition) OS. The installed OS empowers you with a faster, more seamless experience, optimized to save space. You also get smart suggestions and shortcuts that help you do more, and more visibility into and control how you share information on your device.\r\\n\r\\nFor a better user experience, Nokia C12 comes with less bloatware to give you more storage for your things. What’s even better, it also uses less unwanted background data to make your mobile data plan go further. The 64GB 2GB RAM, 64GB 3GB RAM inbuilt memory in addition to MicroSD slot is sufficient on the budget phone to enable downloading of some applications and multi-media files. It combines octa-core processing power and an additional 2 GB of virtual memory, helping to run your apps smoothly.\r\\n<h3>Nokia C12 Network and Communication</h3>\r\\nThe Nokia handset is 4G-enabled, supporting 2G, 3G, and up to 4G network Bandwidth. The uploading and downloading speeds are decent at HSPA, LTE for the 4G-enabled device.\r\\n\r\\nFor ease of communication, Nokia C12 comes equipped with:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>WIFI connectivity</li>\r\\n 	<li>Bluetooth enabled</li>\r\\n 	<li>GPS</li>\r\\n 	<li>FM Radio</li>\r\\n 	<li>Micro USB Port</li>\r\\n 	<li>Accelerometer and Proximity Sensors</li>\r\\n 	<li>5mm jack</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nNokia C12 features a 3,000mAh removable battery. Nokia could have done better, considering most smartphones come with at least 5,000mAh. Taking advantage of the latest battery-saving features and streamlined software, Nokia C12 delivers all-day battery life, hours of talk time or weeks of standby.\r\\n<table>\r\\n<tbody>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Brand</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">Nokia</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Model</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">C21</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Price</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">Kes 11,300</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Availability</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Announced: 18<sup>th</sup> January 2023</li>\r\\n 	<li>Released to the market: from 2<sup>nd</sup> February 2023.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Physical Attributes</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Weight: 177g</li>\r\\n 	<li>Dimensions: 160.6 x 74.3 x 8.8 mm</li>\r\\n 	<li>SIM Cards: dual, stand by</li>\r\\n 	<li>Splash resistant</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Display</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Type: IPS LCD</li>\r\\n 	<li>Size: 6.3 inches</li>\r\\n 	<li>Resolution: 720 x 1600 pixels</li>\r\\n 	<li>Protector: Scratch-resistant glass</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Memory</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Inbuilt memory: 2GB / 3GB RAM,</li>\r\\n 	<li>64GB Internal Memory.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Memory card: Supported</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Camera</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Selfie camera: 5MP</li>\r\\n 	<li>Main Camera: 8MP</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>sensors</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Accelerometer</li>\r\\n 	<li>Proximity sensor</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Communication aiding features</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Bluetooth enabled</li>\r\\n 	<li>Supports WI-FI</li>\r\\n 	<li>FM Radio</li>\r\\n 	<li>3.5mm jack port</li>\r\\n 	<li>Loudspeaker installed</li>\r\\n 	<li>Supports GPS</li>\r\\n 	<li>Micro-USB 2.0</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Battery</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">3,000mAh non-removable battery</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"138\"><strong>Colors</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"486\">Dark Cyan, Charcoal, and Light Mint</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Nokia-C12','Nokia-C12',14500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(114,'Nokia C31','Nokia C31','Nokia-C31','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,8,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Nokia C31','<h2>Nokia C31 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h4>Design, Body and Display</h4>\r\\nBesides its ergonomic design, the Nokia C31 has great aesthetics that appeal to the eye. A massive 6.75-inch and brightly lit screen will catch your eye. The Grey and Blue color variants hide much, considering the device’s capabilities when put to the test. The back and body frame of the Nokia X31 is made of plastic, while the front is predominantly made of glass.\r\\n\r\\nThe handset has a dominant 6.75-inch IPS LCD with a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels, translating to ~260 ppi in terms of density. The IPS LCD screen on the handset has a refresh rate of 60Hz. A 2.5D toughened glass protects the glass. You can enjoy it optimally from the large screen, above-average refresh rate, and average pixel resolution, which is great when playing video games and consuming media on the handset.\r\\n<h4>Cameras</h4>\r\\nCapture important life moments that matter to you with the cameras on the device. The selfie camera consists of a 5MP camera. Nokia could better with this, considering how low the pixelation is, compared to other devices. At the back, capture important life moments and record videos with a triple camera setup consisting of 13 MP (wide), AF + 2 MP, (macro) + 2 MP, (depth). The main camera features a LED Flash and HDR and can capture 1080p@30fps videos.\r\\n<h4>Performance and Battery</h4>\r\\nEnjoy a robust and fast performance on your Nokia C31, running on Android 12 and equipped with Unisoc SC9863A (28nm) chipset. A powerful processing unit is installed on the handset, consisting of an Octa-core (4×1.6 GHz Cortex-A55 &amp; 4×1.2 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU and IMG8322 GPU. You can browse the internet, quickly process data, multi-task, and play low to medium-setting games without experiencing lagging.\r\\n\r\\nNokia C31 comes in 3 variants, giving you great choices based on your need, budget, and preferences. The variants in terms of internal space are models with 32GB 3GB RAM / 64GB 4GB RAM / 128GB 4GB RAM. Additional memory is supported, with the MicroSD card supporting up to 256GB. A 5,050 Li-Po non-removable battery powers the handset. It can stay for three working days before recharge. It supports 10W, 5V/2A Charging.\r\\n<h4>Network and Connectivity</h4>\r\\nNokia C31 is a 4G-enabled handset. With speeds of HSPA 42.2/5.76 Mbps, LTE, and supported by GSM / HSPA / LTE Network Technology, the handset is ideal in the current market for customers demanding fast connectivity, uploading, and downloading of data. Depending on your network provider’s strength, you can use the 2G, 3G, and 4G Bands.\r\\n\r\\nBesides network connectivity, you can transfer data via Bluetooth through Bluetooth pairing, OTG transfer, and data access via the USB Type-C port and NFC. Wireless connectivity is enabled for Wi-Fi and network connectivity. Make use of all these options to enjoy your Nokia C31 device fully. GPS (A-GPS) is enabled on the device for better navigability, especially if you are a motorist and find yourself in unfamiliar regions and need to trace or GET traced. You will find the rear-mounted fingerprint scanner useful in enhancing the security access of your device alongside the Face ID and unlock feature on the front-facing camera.',NULL,NULL,'Nokia-C31','Nokia-C31',18000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(115,'Nokia C32','Nokia C32','Nokia-C32','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,8,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Nokia C32','<h2>Nokia C32 Specifications</h2>\r\\nNokia C32 features a 6.5-inch IPS LCD that refreshes at 60Hz and has a 720 x 1600 pixels resolution. The phone has a dual-camera setup that consists of 50MP + 2MP and an 8MP front camera. It runs on a Unisoc SC9863A1 (22nm) chipset, Octa-core (4×1.6 GHz Cortex-A55 &amp; 4×1.2 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU, and IMG8322 GPU. Operating on an Android 13 OS, the Nokia C31 is available in Charcoal, Autumn Green, and Beach Pink colour variants.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<h3>Physical Attributes of Nokia C32</h3>\r\\n<h4>Body and Design</h4>\r\\nThe phone measures 164.6 x 75.9 x 8.6 mm and weighs 199.4g. Although a bit weighty, you will find it comfortable in your hand and portable once you get used to it.\r\\n\r\\nAs a single SIM phone, the Nokia C32 is made of a glass front, glass back, and plastic frame. The front display glass is protected by a screen protector, always on display.\r\\n\r\\nWith toughened glass on both sides and an inner metal chassis, the Nokia C32 feels reassuringly sleek and sturdy.\r\\n\r\\nThe sleek sandwich design and straight sidewalls give the handset a modern look and feel, elevated even further with the luxurious glass back. Furthermore, the Charcoal, Autumn Green, and Beach Pink colours give the phone elegance and uniqueness, making it classy.\r\\n<h4>Waterproof</h4>\r\\nBe ready to take the Nokia C32 anywhere on the day with you. Its <a href=\"https://www.alpeco.co.nz/downloads/IP%20Rating%20Form.pdf\">IP52 protection</a> rating means the Nokia C32 can hold up against dust and spills.\r\\n<h3>Security</h3>\r\\nWith a fingerprint sensor conveniently built into the power button, the key to quick and secure device unlocking is in your hands. Prefer face unlock? The Nokia C32 has that, too.\r\\n<h3>Display of Nokia C32</h3>\r\\nNokia C32 features a 720 x 1600 pixels waterdrop screen that is bright enough to enjoy using as you play games, watch videos and work. The 6.5-inch IPS LCD screen is protected by scratch-resistant glass, making it less vulnerable to scratches that usually affect the viewing experience on your display. A default 60Hz refresh does the job, but it is not good enough for the best immersive experience compared to other phones, such as Redmi Note 12 4G or Samsung Galaxy F04.\r\\n<h3>Camera Set up</h3>\r\\nCapture every epic moment with the camera set up on the Nokia C32. The primary dual camera (50MP + 2MP) and front-facing 8MP camera for selfies are great for modest, quality photos and 1080p videos.\r\\n\r\\nGood lighting doesn’t wait around the perfect shot. That’s why the Nokia C32 features a dual rear camera with a 50 MP main sensor to capture more light. Coupled with the built-in imaging algorithms, you’ll get stellar shots, day or night. Besides, with Night mode and Portrait mode for both the rear and selfie cameras, you can capture the action on either side of the phone.\r\\n<h3>Nokia C32’s Performance</h3>\r\\nRunning on Android 13 OS, you will have no dull moment as the phone runs its up-to-date applications and systems smoothly. The phone is complete with the latest personalization, security and privacy features. And with less bloatware, there’s more free space for your stuff.\r\\n\r\\nAndroid 13 has many features to make your smartphone experience smoother and more personal. Moreover, you can open and switch between more applications with a memory extension that turns 2 GB of storage space into device memory.\r\\n\r\\nThe processing power on the phone is impressive for multitasking, gaming and video streaming without worries. Specifically, it comes packed with an Octa-core CPU, Unisoc SC9863A1 (22nm) Chipset and IMG8322 GPU. They work together to ensure the best user experience, excellent battery power management, and less overheating under intensive use.\r\\n\r\\nWith an internal memory of 64GB 3GB RAM / 64GB 4GB RAM / 128GB 4GB RAM, you are not limited on performance or storage space as you put the phone to the task. For a budget phone, 3GB/4 GB is reasonable and will get the phone quickly processing data without lags and stutters. Besides, with up to 128GB ROM and a MicroSDXC (dedicated slot), space for storing your photos, videos and downloads is ample.\r\\n<h3>Network and Connectivity</h3>\r\\nThe 4G network-enabled handset has excellent connectivity capabilities, supporting 2G, 3G and 4G brands.\r\\n\r\\nUse Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n for internet connectivity, and upgrade the system to download your favourite applications in record time.\r\\n\r\\nBluetooth connectivity via the phone’s BT 5.2, A2DP provides a fast, seamless pairing experience with your other devices like EarPods, BT Headsets and Smartwatch as you stay connected wirelessly.\r\\n\r\\nThe 3.5mm jack is equally great for listening to your MP3 Hits, radio shows and YouTube videos once you plug in your earphones or wired headsets.\r\\n\r\\nGPS is also installed on the handset, enabling accurate location and tracking wherever you are.\r\\n<h3>Battery of Nokia C32</h3>\r\\nA Li-Po 5,000 mAh, non-removable battery is incredible any day! Such a massive battery on a lavish budget phone ensures you have no dull moment as you browse through your gallery, take photos, search the internet and immerse yourself in watching your favourite series or playing games.\r\\n\r\\nWith the latest battery-saving features like app hibernation and HMD Super battery saver, the Nokia C32 can go up to 3 days between charges. Plus, its streamlined OS means less bloatware using up power in the background.\r\\n\r\\nThe 10W wired charger ensures your phone is always powered on within the shortest time possible, and you are back on it whatever you were engaged in before going low on power.',NULL,NULL,'Nokia-C32','Nokia-C32',18000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(116,'Nokia G11 Plus','Nokia G11 Plus','Nokia-G11-Plus','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,8,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Nokia G11 Plus','<h2>Nokia G11 Plus Features and Specifications</h2>\r\\n<h4>Nokia G11 Plus Overview</h4>\r\\nThe Nokia G11 Plus flaunts a 6.52-inch IPS LCD with a 90Hz refresh rate. It gets powered by an Octa-core, Unisoc T606 (12 nm), and a 5,000mAh battery unit. On the optics, the phone has an 8MP selfie camera at the front and a dual-rear 50MP+2MP camera setup. It also offers a rear-mounted fingerprint scanner. The device comes in Lake Blue and Charcoal Grey color variants.\r\\n\r\\n<iframe title=\"Nokia G11 Plus. For life, wherever it may take you\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/OdBkV3l6OwU?feature=oembed&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https://www.phoneplacekenya.com\" width=\"1170\" height=\"658\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe>\r\\n<h4>Design, Body Build, and Display</h4>\r\\nNokia G11 Plus is sleek and beautifully designed with rounded edges and relatively flat surfaces. The front of the handset has a prominent 6.52-inches IPS LCD, which features a water-drop notch, where the selfie camera is located. The device features a dual camera set-up at the back, where you can take great picture shots and videos.\r\\n\r\\nThe G11 Plus measures 164.8 x 75.9 x 8.6 mm and weighs 192g. The device’s body is made of plastic at the back, with a plastic body frame and a glass front. The 6.52-inches display of the Nokia phone is made of IPS LCD with a 90Hz refresh rate to keep the device’s screen in peak performance. The screen-to-body ratio on the device is 82.1%, with a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels (~269 ppi density). It is not one of the brightest screens compared to other devices, but it will get the job done in terms of optimal user experience.\r\\n<h4>Processing Unit</h4>\r\\nThe handset features an Octa-core (2×1.6 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.6 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU, with a <a href=\"https://www.notebookcheck.net/UNISOC-Tiger-T606-Processor-Benchmarks-and-Specs.582689.0.html\">Unisoc T606</a> (12 nm) chipset and Mali-G57 MP1 GPU running on the Android 12 Operating System. The processor is robust and reliable for enabling multi-tasking and playing basic games on the device. The 3GB RAM 32GB / 64GB 3GB / 64GB 4GB internal memory space is sufficient to run basic applications and some preferred downloaded applications. The MicroSD expandable option is worthwhile, considering the user needs unlimited space to download and consume media (text and video).\r\\n<h4>Battery Capacity</h4>\r\\nA 5,00mAh Li-Po non-removable battery is massive for the Nokia handset, considering other Nokia devices which have characteristically low power capacity. The battery capacity is excellent for optimal usage of the Nokia G11 Plus, without the frequent inconveniences caused by low battery. Fast charging of the battery charging is achieved through a wired 67W wired adapter, which is a valuable inclusion for users.\r\\n<h4>Connectivity</h4>\r\\nThe Nokia smartphone is a 4G-enabled device that supports GSM/ HSPA/ LTE 4G Network, supporting up to 4G Bands with HSPA 42.2/5.76 Mbps, LTE Cat4 150/50 Mbps speed. It supports Wi-Fi connectivity, with Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot specifications. You can use your phone with other devices through Bluetooth, with the Nokia device boasting 5.0, A2DP, and LE specifications. The USB Type-C 2.0, USB On-The-Go enables charging and transfer of data to other devices. For convenience, the phone is equipped with several sensors. It features a Fingerprint sensor (rear-mounted), Accelerometer, Proximity Sensor, and GPS (A-GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO) for easy navigation and location tracking.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-2883\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-2883\" aria-describedby=\"tablepress-2883-description\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Nokia</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Nokia G11 Plus</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-4\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Announced</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">2022, June 29</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-5\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Released</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">2022, June 29</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-6\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Operating System</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Android 12</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-7\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Chipset</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Unisoc T606 (12 nm)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-8\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>CPU Speed</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Octa-core (2×1.6 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.6 GHz Cortex-A55)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-9\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPU Graphics Processor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Mali-G57 MP1</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-10\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Storage</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>32GB/64GB</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-11\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>RAM</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>3GB/4GB</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-12\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Card Slot</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>microSDXC (dedicated slot)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-13\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Rear Camera</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>50 MP + 2 MP</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-14\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Front Camera</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>8 MP</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-15\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Network</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>GSM / HSPA / LTE</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-16\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sim Card</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Single SIM (Nano-SIM) or Dual SIM (Nano-SIM, dual stand-by)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-17\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Weight</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">192 g (6.77 oz)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-18\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Dimensions</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">164.8 x 75.9 x 8.6 mm (6.49 x 2.99 x 0.34 in)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-19\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Screen Resolution</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">720 x 1600 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~269 ppi density)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-20\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Type</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">IPS LCD, 90Hz, 400 nits (typ)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-21\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Size</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>6.52 inches, 102.6 cm2 (~82.1% screen-to-body ratio)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-22\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>3.5mm jack</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Yes</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-23\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Bluetooth</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">5.0, A2DP, LE</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-24\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPS</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Yes, with A-GPS</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-25\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>NFC</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>No</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-26\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, hotspot</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-27\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>USB</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">USB Type-C 2.0, USB On-The-Go</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-28\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Radio</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>FM Radio</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-29\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sensor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Fingerprint (rear-mounted), accelerometer, proximity</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-30\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Battery</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Li-Ion 5000 mAh, non-removable</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-31\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Colors</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Lake Blue, Charcoal Grey</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Nokia-G11-Plus','Nokia-G11-Plus',19000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(117,'Nokia T20','Nokia T20','Nokia-T20','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,8,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Nokia T20','<h2>Nokia T20 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h4>Unboxing and Design</h4>\r\\nThe first and most obvious question is what do you get in the box of the Nokia T20? And the answer is a charger, a USB cable type C, and about 10 trees worth of starter guides. And that’s it for the box. Nice and straightforward. First impressions of the T20 tablet. It is obviously a budget device but it does feel a little bit more premium than Amazon’s Fire HD 10 for instance.\r\\n\r\\n<iframe title=\"Nokia T20 - A tablet designed to last\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/31Fb0cgdqEM?feature=oembed&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https://www.phoneplacekenya.com\" width=\"1170\" height=\"658\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe>\r\\n\r\\nThe plastic back looks rather nice. It could almost pass as metal, got a matte finish which hopefully should repel the worst of finger greasings. Definitely feels solidly put together. You’ve got toughened glass upfront as well. Just to help give it an extra bit of protection. This tablet is surprisingly lightweight as well. It has got nicely rounded corners with a strange positioning of the headphone Jack which is actually stuck away at its bottom right corner.\r\\n<h4>Display</h4>\r\\nNow, the Nokia T20 rocks very respectable 10.4-inch displays of 2000 x 1200 pixel resolutions. Its visuals are reasonably crisp despite the fact that it’s obviously quite a spacious screen. Certainly, you’ve got enough. It is just a simple IPS panel. So don’t expect super sharp contrast and unrealistically vivid colors. And it maxes out at 400 nits (typ) which is fine for indoor use. The view angles are good enough. Sadly there is no way to change the refresh rate though. It is stuck at 60 Hertz. And the Nokia T20 has a stereo speaker arrangement. Both of those speakers are housed on the edge of the tablet. And it’s a reasonably good audio setup. There’s a clear distinction between the left and the right channels. Decent clarity as well.\r\\n<h4>Platform</h4>\r\\nHMD global has not tinkered with Android here. It’s a stock version of Android 11 on the Nokia T20. The main difference is that the Google feed is heavily focused on video, games, and stuff to read. As well on the video side of things, you can get recommendations to watch from the likes of YouTube, Disney Plus, etc. But it does not have Netflix support even though it is fully customizable. It’s quite a limited selection, but a pretty good way of just seeing some of the latest releases on various platforms.\r\\n<h4>Extra features</h4>\r\\nAnother feature that HMD has added to the Nokia T20 on top of Android is Face Unlock. You’ve also got Kid Space loaded on here. And as always one of the benefits for Nokia devices is the fact you’ve got guaranteed updates stretching into the future two years of all OS updates. What this means is that you will be getting Android 12 later on. And then Android 13 after that and three years of security updates as well. This Nokia T20 has 64 GB of storage to play with here. There is a 32 GB variant in some regions as well. But the good news is you can expand that via an SD card if you like.\r\\n<h4>Performance</h4>\r\\nNow performance as you’d expect, it’s fairly basic here on the Nokia T20 as it is just a budget tablet. Power comes courtesy of the Unisoc T610 (12 nm) chipset that offers basic platform performance. But the T20 certainly seems up to the job for simple stuff like streaming videos, browsing the internet, and so on. The great thing is that the tablet shows no signs of heating up as you would expect from a basic chipset.\r\\n\r\\nWhat we must be thankful for is its 64GB internal storage, and especially that beefy 4GB RAM it comes with. The 32GB vraiant has 3GB RAM. And stuffed inside of the T20 is a Li-Po 8200 mAh, non-removable battery. It should keep you going all day long depending on what you are using to tablet for. It supports Fast charging 15W.\r\\n<h4>Cameras</h4>\r\\nYes Nokia T20 has a selfie built into the top end of the display there when you’re holding it in a landscape. This one should do fine for your video chats as its large display keeps your face reasonably bright. You’ve also got the rear camera here. It is an 8 MP, AF shooter and that is just about what I can say about it.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<table class=\"mdl-data-table mdl-js-data-table\" data-upgraded=\",MaterialDataTable\">\r\\n<tbody>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"></td>\r\\n<td></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Display</strong></td>\r\\n<td>10.4 inch</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>OS</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Android 11</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Sim Card</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Dual SIM</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Colors</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Deep Ocean</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Radio</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Wireless FM radio</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>RAM</strong></td>\r\\n<td>4GB</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Storage</strong></td>\r\\n<td>64GB</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td class=\"mdl-data-table__cell--non-numeric\"><strong>Battery</strong></td>\r\\n<td>Li-Ion 8200 mAh</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Nokia-T20','Nokia-T20',23000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(118,'Oppo A17','Oppo A17','Oppo-A17','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A17','<h2 class=\"short-title\">Oppo A17 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h4>Design, Body Build, and Display</h4>\r\\nOPPO A17 measures 164.2 x 75.6 x 8.3 mm and weighs 189g. The device’s body is made of plastic at the back, a plastic body frame, and a glass front. The 6.56-inch IPS display of the Oppo handset has a refresh rate of 60 Hz and a resolution of 720 x 1612 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~269 PPI density). It is an average resolution for both work and plays on your device.\r\\n<h4>Performance and Battery</h4>\r\\nThe handset has a 5,000mAh removable Li-PO battery powering it. It supports up to a 4G network and is ideal for calls, texts, and playing games pre-installed on the device. Enjoy FM Radio on the device as you commute or work and connect to other devices via Bluetooth and WiFi.a 3.5mm jack will enable you to access your FM Radio and media entertainment on the Oppo A17 hands-free.\r\\n\r\\nInstalled on the device is a MediaTek MT6765 <a href=\"https://www.mediatek.com/products/smartphones-2/mediatek-helio-g35\">Helio G35</a> (12 nm). Running applications and commands in the background is a powerful Octa-core (4×2.3 GHz Cortex-A53 &amp; 4×1.8 GHz Cortex-A53) CPU and PowerVR GE8320 GPU. To ensure you do not run out of space and your device operates optimally, Oppo installed 64GB 4GB RAM internal memory on their A17 handset, using eMMC 5.1 technology to maximize space.\r\\n<h4>Camera</h4>\r\\nOppo A17 invested in its cameras to give users an above-average camera setup experience. The front camera features a single, 5 MP, f/2.2, (wide) camera for selfies and video chats. It will certainly get the job done, considering it has the HDR feature and can take videos. At the back, capture moments and life experiences using a massive 50 MP, f/1.8, (wide), PDAF + 2 MP, f/2.4, (depth) camera setup. The main camera can take 1080p@30fps video shots using LED flash, HDR, and panorama for professional-looking photos and videos.\r\\n<h4>Connectivity and Sensors</h4>\r\\nOppo A17 is a 4G-network-enabled device. Enjoy fast upload and download speeds, depending on the signal strength of your network provider. For convenience, Oppo installed several sensors on its handset: Fingerprint (side-mounted), accelerometer, proximity\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-2223\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-2223\" aria-describedby=\"tablepress-2223-description\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Oppo</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Oppo A17</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-4\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Announced</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>2022</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-5\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Released</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>2022</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-6\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Operating System</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Android 12; Color OS 12</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-7\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Chipset</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Mediatek Helio P35</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-8\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>CPU Speed</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Octa-core 2.3 GHz Cortex-A53</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-9\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPU Graphics Processor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>PowerVR GE8320 (680 MHz)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-10\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Storage</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>64GB</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-11\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>RAM</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div><a href=\"https://www.phone