O, BDS</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-23\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>NFC</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>No</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-24\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-25\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>USB</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>2.0, Type-C 1.0 reversible connector, USB On-The-Go</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-26\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Radio</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>FM Radio</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-27\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sensor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Fingerprint (rear-mounted), accelerometer, gyro, proximity</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-28\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Battery</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Li-Po 5000 mAh, non-removable</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-29\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Colors</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Midnight Black, Lake Blue</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A17','Oppo-A17',22000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(119,'Oppo A17K','Oppo A17K','Oppo-A17K','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A17K','<h2>Oppo A17K Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h4>Design, Body Build, and Display</h4>\r\\nOPPO A17k measures 164.2 x 75.6 x 8.3 mm and weighs 189g. The device’s body is made of plastic at the back, a plastic body frame, and a glass front. The 6.56-inch IPS display of the Oppo handset has a refresh rate of 60Hz and a resolution of 720 x 1612 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~269 PPI density). It is an average resolution for both work and plays on your device.\r\\n<h4>Performance and Battery</h4>\r\\nThe handset has a 5,000mAh removable Li-PO battery powering it. It supports up to a 4G network and is ideal for calls, texts, and playing games pre-installed on the device. Enjoy FM Radio on the device as you commute or work and connect to other devices via Bluetooth and WiFi. A 3.5mm jack will enable you to access your FM Radio and media entertainment on the Oppo A17k hands-free.\r\\n\r\\nInstalled on the device is a MediaTek MT6765 <a href=\"https://www.mediatek.com/products/smartphones-2/mediatek-helio-g35\">Helio G35</a> (12 nm). Running applications and commands in the background is a decent Octa-core (4×2.3 GHz Cortex-A53 &amp; 4×1.8 GHz Cortex-A53) CPU and PowerVR GE8320 GPU. To ensure you do not run out of space and your device operates optimally, Oppo installed 64GB 3GB RAM internal memory on their A17k handset, using eMMC 5.1 technology to maximize space.\r\\n<h4>Camera</h4>\r\\nOppo A17k is a downgraded version of the Oppo A17. The front camera features a single, 5 MP, f/2.2 (wide) camera for selfies and video chats. The front camera’s power is glaringly low, even though it can capture 1080p@30fps.\r\\n\r\\nAt the back, capture moments and life experiences using a massive single, 8 MP, f/2.0, (wide), AF. With capabilities of 1080p@30fps, you will be able to capture moments in still and motion, but a lot is left to be desired. Supported by LED flash and panorama, the 8MP lens needs to catch up to the best standards in the modern-day mobile world of cameras.\r\\n<h4>Connectivity and Sensors</h4>\r\\nOppo A17 is a 4G-network-enabled device. Enjoy fast upload and download speeds, depending on the signal strength of your network provider. For convenience, Oppo installed several sensors on its handset: Fingerprint (side-mounted), accelerometer, Proximity, and Compass',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A17K','Oppo-A17K',19000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(120,'Oppo A18','Oppo A18','Oppo-A18','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A18','<h2>Oppo A18 Specificatons in Kenya</h2>\r\\nThe Oppo A18 price in Kenya is Kes 20,600. It features a 6.56-inch LCD with HD+ resolution and has a water-drop notch and sizable bezels around the screen. Under the hood, the device has a MediaTek Helio G35 powering the device with 4GB of RAM and 128GB of storage. The smartphone has a dual camera setup on the back with an 8MP primary camera and a 2MP depth sensor. We get a 5MP (wide) selfie camera with fixed focus. Oppo A18 draws power from a 5,000mAh battery with some features to extend battery life, including Super Power Saving Mode and Super Nighttime Standby. Other notable specs include the Android 13 Operating System, ColorOS 13.1 UI, IP54 water resistance rating, USB Type-C 2.0, and OTG for charging and data transfer. It is available in Glowing Black and Glowing Blue colours.\r\\n<h3>Design and Build</h3>\r\\nOppo A18 is the ideal budget phone you have been waiting for, coming along as part of the long Oppo A series of phones. It measures 163.7 x 75 x 8.2 mm (6.44 x 2.95 x 0.32 in) and weighs 188g. the dual SIM phone is IP54 rated, being dust and splash-resistant.\r\\n\r\\nUnlock your potential and enhance your phone security with the reliable Side Fingerprint Unlock. The fingerprint scanner serves as the power button on the Oppo A18.\r\\n\r\\nAdd a touch of class to every day with the sophisticated, high-end 2D design. Then, get straight into the on-screen action, thanks to the rapid-fire side fingerprint unlock function.\r\\n<h3>The Oppo Glow Design</h3>\r\\nOppo’s modern, shimmering take on classic black features a string of pearl design highlighting your camera. Dive into the shifting depths of glowing blue, like light on the shimmering seas of a perfect summer’s day. The two colours for Oppo A18 (Glowing Black Glowing Blue) complement your style, elegance and sophistication.\r\\n<h3>Oppo a18’s Display</h3>\r\\nBrighten Up Your Day with the 90Hz Sunlight Display on the 6.56 IPS LCD screen. The bigger, brighter screen gives you excellent colour and a rapid refresh rate, immersing you in awesome on-screen action that flows seamlessly from second to second.\r\\n\r\\nAt 720 x 1612 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~269 ppi density) resolution, the 6.56-inch display is good but could be better with 1080p resolution, allowing for better user experience. Nevertheless, the 269 ppi density is good enough for video viewing, content consumption, internet browsing and social media interactions.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<h3>Camera Set up on Oppo A18</h3>\r\\nOppo A18 has a slightly average set of cameras. It packs;\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>5 MP, f/2.2, (wide) selfie camera that records 1080p videos</li>\r\\n 	<li>Primary camera consisting of two lenses: 8 MP, f/2.0, (wide), AF + 2 MP, f/2.4, (depth). The primary camera equally records 1080p videos.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nWith both, you can record decent pictures and record 1080p videos. However, you will have a lesser quality experience than other smartphones like the Oppo A98 and Oppo A58, which pack superior cameras and record up to 4K videos.',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A18','Oppo-A18',19000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(121,'Oppo A18 - 128GB','Oppo A18 - 128GB','Oppo-A18-128GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A18 - 128GB','Oppo A18 - 128GB',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A18-128GB','Oppo-A18-128GB',21000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(122,'Oppo A18 - 64GB','Oppo A18 - 64GB','Oppo-A18-64GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A18 - 64GB','Oppo A18 - 64GB',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A18-64GB','Oppo-A18-64GB',19500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(123,'Oppo A38','Oppo A38','Oppo-A38','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A38','<h2>Oppo A38</h2>\r\\nOppo A38 has a 6.56” LCD with HD+ resolution, up to 90 Hz refresh rate, and a 90 Hz touch sampling rate. There is also a waterdrop notch for the selfie camera with a 5 MP sensor behind. Two cameras are on the back, but only the main one is useful. It is 50 MP with f/1.8 aperture and autofocus. The second one is a 2 MP depth sensor. The chipset is Mediatek Helio G85, and the phone has 4 GB RAM and 128 GB storage. The micro-SD slot enables up to 1 TB of extra storage.\r\\n\r\\nOppo equipped the A38 with a 5,000 mAh battery that supports 33W SuperVOOC charging and basic PD (9V/1.5A). The Oppo A38 will get updates for 2.5 years, which is a good thing, given that this phone is on the more affordable end of the price spectrum. The dual SIM capabilities, a 3.5 mm audio jack, the latest Bluetooth 5.3, and all major GNSS standards are other features. The Oppo A38 is arriving in two Glowing colours – Black and Gold, but we have no information on pricing or availability.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<h3>Build and Design of Oppo A38</h3>\r\\nOppo’s glow design makes its handsets stand out. Oppo A38’s glittering high-end textures draw every eye to your phone whenever you take it out. Choose the glowing Gold for a flash of sunlight and shimmering halos.\r\\n\r\\nIt is built to last, with a body made of a plastic body frame and back and glass front. Being IP54 rated, the phone is dust and splash-resistant. With good care, it will last many years before the need for replacement.\r\\n\r\\nDimension-wise, the device measures 163.7 x 75 x 8.2 mm and weighs 190g. reasonably, it is comfortable to hold and use with one hand and carry in the pocket. At 190g, you will feel its weight slightly, but you will get used to it.\r\\n<h4>Display</h4>\r\\nThe handset features a large, water-drop, 6.56-inch IPS LCD, 90Hz, 720 nits (peak).  The 720 x 1612 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~269 ppi density) is a bit of a let-down to an otherwise great mid-range phone if you are running on a tight budget.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<h3>Cameras for Photography and Video Recording</h3>\r\\nOppo A38 comes fully installed with front and back-end cameras for an excellent photography experience.\r\\n<h4>Selfie Camera</h4>\r\\nThe selfie camera consists of an average 5MP (wide) camera.  Although functional and capable of recording 1080p videos, its output is limited, putting you as a high-quality selfie lover on the edge.\r\\n<h4>Oppo A38 Main Camera</h4>\r\\nAt the rear end, the phone packs a dual camera set-up consisting of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>50 MP, f/1.8, (wide), PDAF lens</li>\r\\n 	<li>2 MP, f/2.4, (depth)</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nBoth lenses combine to provide above-average, AI-enhanced photo shots and 1080p videos that you will love as you share with family and friends and equally store for memories.\r\\n<h4>Amazing Portraits</h4>\r\\nBecome a photography pro by unveiling new levels of beauty and detail in your pictures with prominent images from the 50MP AI Camera.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>AI Portrait Re-touch: </strong>Restore your most beautiful, natural looks with the help of upgraded AI Portrait Retouching.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Portrait Bokeh:</strong> Put your subjects front and centre, as Portrait Mode places people in the middle of the picture.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<h3>Connectivity on Oppo A38</h3>\r\\nRegarding connectivity, the Oppo phone does not fall short by any means. As a modern-day smartphone, it comes equipped with:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Fast HSPA, LTE 4G Network speeds, supporting 2G, 3G and 4G Networks</li>\r\\n 	<li>Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band for fast internet connectivity</li>\r\\n 	<li>3, A2DP, LE, aptX HD version for seamless Bluetooth pairing</li>\r\\n 	<li>GPS, GALILEO, GLONASS, BDS, and QZSS for accurate location pinpointing</li>\r\\n 	<li>USB Type-C 2.0, OTG for fast, wired connectivity to other devices.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Performance</h3>\r\\n<h4>Super-efficient Processor</h4>\r\\nRun smoother operations for longer on the Oppo A38. A dedicated gaming chipset and smart computing engine maintain peak performance under pressure. Plus, ‘like new’ phone performance lasts longer with 36-month fluency tests passed in style.\r\\n\r\\nThe handset is well equipped with <a href=\"https://www.mediatek.com/products/smartphones-2/mediatek-helio-g85\">Mediatek MT6769 Helio G85</a> (12nm) chipset, Octa-core (2×2.0 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.8 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU and Mali-G52 MC2 GPU, all of which make a robust, reliable and efficient processor for multi-tasking and playing gaming without lags and stutters, especially on intensive use.\r\\n\r\\nOppo comes packed with 128GB internal memory and 4GB RAM. Such memory is considerable for a budget/ mid-range phone with great features that rival most flagship phones\r\\n<h4>Latest Operating System</h4>\r\\nOf course, the Oppo phone comes with the latest Android 13 OS, complemented with the impressive Oppo’s  ColorOS 13.1, which allows applications’ customisation and makes you at ease as you explore the Oppo easy, colour-rich, beyond-imagination world through its friendly, upgraded User Interface.\r\\n<h3>Oppo A38’s Battery and Charging</h3>\r\\nA 33W SUPERVOOC charging unit recharges the massive 5,000mAh battery on the Oppo A38. The 33W PD recharges 1-50% in 30 min. Whether you need to hit the shops, make a meetup or be there for your besties, speedy charging and a reliable battery will see your phone ready to be there in a flash.',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A38','Oppo-A38',25000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(124,'Oppo A58','Oppo A58','Oppo-A58','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A58','<h2>Oppo A58 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\nOppo A58  comprises a 6.72-inch IPS LCD Display with a refresh rate of 90Hz. Weighing 192g, the ergonomically designed and beautiful-looking Oppo A58 measures 165.7 x 76 x 8 mm. It makes the Oppo A58 both easy to handle when using and portable as far as weight is concerned.\r\\n\r\\nThe front display Oppo A48 4G features a button-hole feature that accommodates the front-facing single, 8 MP, f/2.0, 26mm (wide) selfie camera. At the rear end of the phone, it packs a dual-camera set-up consisting of 50MP + 2MP lenses, besides the plastic cover enclosing the non-removable 5,000mAh battery.\r\\n\r\\nGet the best experience on the Oppo A58 4G, powered by an Octa-core, Mediatek MT6769 Helio G85 (12nm) processor and relying on Android 13, ColorOS 13.1. The 128GB internal memory 6GB RAM is sufficient, besides the dedicated MicroSD slot for additional memory. Now available in Glowing Black and Dazzling Green.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nBoasting a 6.72-inch IPS LCD, sufficient display space will undoubtedly impress and encourage you to dig in more. The 1080 x 2400 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~392 ppi density) resolution adds to the glowing tributes on the impressive Oppo A58 4G. 1080p resolution should be the standard for mid-range smartphones, which Oppo A58 4G is.\r\\n\r\\nTo compensate for the 720p resolution, Oppo further complemented the 1080p resolution on the wide 6.72-inch IPS LCD with above-average 550 nits (typ) and 680 nits (HBM) display brightness. Moreover, a 90Hz refresh rate is excellent in keeping the display in peak performance and giving you an uncompromised, immersive experience as you play games and watch videos.\r\\n<h3>Performance of Oppo A58 4G</h3>\r\\nThe internal space comprising 128GB internal memory (ROM) and 6GB RAM is sufficient for users and enables optimal device performance. Running on Android 13 OS, with ColorOS 13.1 for customization, Oppo A58 4G comes packed with the latest applications and upgrades for optimal user experience.\r\\n\r\\nTo ensure efficiency and prompt response to commands, Oppo packs a reliable and efficient Mediatek MT6769 Helio G85 (12nm) chipset that enables seamless multi-tasking and pushing the device to its limits without it lagging or heating up.\r\\n\r\\nBacking up the impressive chipset is an Octa-core (2×2.0 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.8 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU and <a href=\"https://developer.arm.com/Processors/Mali-G52\">Mali-G52 MC2</a> GPU, all of which make the Oppo A58 4G a powerful, fast and productive handset to have and utilize on tasks and entertainment.\r\\n<h3>Cameras</h3>\r\\nOppo A58 4G packs a single, 8 MP, f/2.0, (wide) camera capable of taking good selfies and recording 1080p@30fps videos.\r\\n\r\\nAt the rear, it packs the primary camera, consisting of a double integrated camera set-up comprising a 50 MP, f/1.8, 27mm (wide), PDAF camera + 2 MP, f/2.4, (depth) lens. The user will capture decent photo shots with a 50 MP, f/1.8, (wide), AF + 2 MP, f/2.4, (depth) lens. With the LED flash, HDR, and panorama, you can choose how best to take your pictures based on lighting, occasion and desired scenery in the background.\r\\n\r\\nBesides enabling you to take incredible, high-quality pictures, the primary camera records 1080p@30fps videos.\r\\n<h3>Sensors on Oppo A58 4G</h3>\r\\nA fingerprint (side-mounted) sensor, accelerometer, proximity, and compass sensors are installed on the handset. They help better handle the Oppo A58 when taking pictures videos, communicating or other functions such as enhancing the phone security.\r\\n<h3>Network</h3>\r\\nThe handset is 4G enabled, with up to HSPA, LTE-A, and network speed. Although it is not 5G enabled, the data uploading and downloading speeds are somewhat impressive, better than 3G bandwidth. Depending on the strength of the network, the phone supports 2G, 3G, and up to 4G Bands.\r\\n<h3>Battery and Charging Oppo 58 4G</h3>\r\\nOppo A58 4G is powered by a 5,000mAh battery and supports fast charging. It comes along with a 33W adapter. You can fast charge the battery by 1-56% in 30 minutes. Unfortunately, the charging system on the phone does not support wireless charging or reverse charging.',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A58','Oppo-A58',35000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(125,'Oppo A58 - 6GB','Oppo A58 - 6GB','Oppo-A58-6GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A58 - 6GB','Oppo A58 - 6GB',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A58-6GB','Oppo-A58-6GB',28500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(126,'Oppo A58 - 8GB','Oppo A58 - 8GB','Oppo-A58-8GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A58 - 8GB','Oppo A58 - 8GB',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A58-8GB','Oppo-A58-8GB',35000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(127,'Oppo A78','Oppo A78','Oppo-A78','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A78','<h2>Oppo A78</h2>\r\\nOppo A78  has a 6.56″ HD+ LCD with a 90Hz refresh rate and 600 nits peak brightness. The Oppo A78 4G comes with 6GB RAM, which can be expanded virtually up to 5GB. You get 128GB of storage onboard, and the smartphone also has a microSD card slot for storage expansion. The phone is powered by the MediaTek Helio G35 SoC and runs ColorOS 12.1 out of the box. Fueling the entire package is a 5,000 mAh battery with 33W charging support, advertised to charge 53% in 30 minutes and 100% in 69 minutes. The A77 4G comes in Sunset Orange (leather), and Sky Blue colors.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<h3>Oppo A78 Physical Phone Attributes</h3>\r\\n<h4>Design</h4>\r\\nLeap into modern looks. Shine bright with diamond light, with the Diamond Matrix Design on the Oppo A78. Dive into the dreamy, rippling, and shimmering diamond textures, with this first-of-its-kind design for Oppo. This stunning phone is a sure-fire style statement, reminiscent of sunlight through crystal clear waters.\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>\r\\n<h5><strong>Iconic Imaging Module Minimalist Runaway Design</strong></h5>\r\\n</li>\r\\n 	<li>: This dynamic, fashion-forward design feature would be right at home on the catwalk. The contrasting texture of this smart glossy strip highlights the professional camera module and creates a modern, minimalist vibe.</li>\r\\n 	<li>\r\\n<h5><strong>Featherlight And Fabulous Ultra Slim Retro Design:</strong></h5>\r\\nClean lines and sharp finishes underpin this cool retro design. Weighing the same as 3 eggs and a whole lot less fragile, the ultra-slim body is as elegant as it is durable, feeling almost weightless in your pocket or hand. Measuring 160 x 73.2 x 7.9 mm and weighing 180g, the Appo A78 feels featherlight and slim in your palm.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h4>Colors</h4>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li><strong>Mist Black:</strong> Oppo’s Mist Black is so much more than pure black, adding the 3D depth of atmospheric thunderclouds and the shimmering luster of a lake’s surface at night to delight your eyes.</li>\r\\n 	<li><strong>Aqua Green:</strong> Taking inspiration from shimmering lakes and sultry seas, this shade has a calm energy that will give you an instant connection to the beauty of the natural world.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h4>IP54 rating</h4>\r\\nDribbled your drink? The IP54 rating means this phone can handle everyday “oops” moments when something splashes on your phone, offering protection from every direction.\r\\n<h3>Oppo A78 Display</h3>\r\\n<h4>Immersive Experience</h4>\r\\nLeap into incredible experience with Oppo A78’s 6.43 inch, AMOLED, 90Hz, 430 nits display. Get immersed in the incredible FHD+ AMOLED display boasting 1080 x 2400 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~409 ppi density) resolution.\r\\n<h4>Phone unlock Feature</h4>\r\\nUnlock the amazing phone with the In-Display Fingerprint Unlock feature. The Oppo A78 4G features a newly upgraded in-display Fingerprint Unlock which makes the frame design sleeker without compromising on your favourite efficiency feature.\r\\n<h4>Eye Comfort Display</h4>\r\\nSee, even in the sunlight, with a screen that can reach a super bright 600nit. Then let the Smart Backlight adjust to your environment, keeping your eyes comfortable and kicking tiredness into the touch.\r\\n<h4>Screen Protection</h4>\r\\nProtecting the immersive, high-resolution display from scratches and breakage due to accidental falls or pressure on the screen is Corning Gorilla Glass 5.\r\\n<h3>Camera Set-up</h3>\r\\nThe trio of amazing cameras has all bases covered, from the 50MP AI Main Camera and dedicated Depth Camera taking in every memory in minute detail, to the HDR-supported Selfie Camera capturing your lovely smile to perfection.\r\\n<h4>Ultra-Imaging, Zero Effort Ultra-Clear 108MP Images</h4>\r\\nTake professional-looking pictures, with minimal input required. Super smart tech stitches together multiple images captured to create an extra clear, ultra-detailed 108MP super high-definition photo.\r\\n<h4>Dual View Video</h4>\r\\nIt’s time to get creative. Shoot from the front and back camera at the same time to create amazing dual-view videos, for family sharing, vlogging, and just for fun with your friends.\r\\n<h4>Quality Audio Output</h4>\r\\nImmerse yourself in music and movies, even in noisy situations, with the upgraded Dual Stereo Speakers and Ultra Volume Mode that can increase volume to 300%. Real HD Sound tunes your sound perfectly for gaming, watching, dancing to your favourite tracks and more. The 3.5mm jack port makes entertainment more fun as you can simply plug in your wired earphones and get into the groove.\r\\n<h3>Opp A78 Processing Power and Performance</h3>\r\\n<h4>Maximised Phone Memory</h4>\r\\nRAM-p Up Performance is superb, especially with 8GB + 8GB RAM Expansion. Use up to a massive 8GB of storage memory as RAM to increase your phone’s performance and run all your apps super smoothly, no matter how full-on your life gets. The 128GB 8GB RAM / 256GB 8GB RAM depending on the model of your choice comes along with a MicroSD slot for additional memory.\r\\n<h4>Raw Processing Power</h4>\r\\nMaximize your experience with the Qualcomm SM6225 Snapdragon 680 4G (6 nm) chipset. Play, listen, watch, film and photograph, enjoying every moment in life perfectly, with the optimized smoothness of Snapdragon’s top-quality 4G chip. The chip comes along with Adeno 610 GPU and Octa-core (4×2.4 GHz Kryo 265 Gold &amp; 4×1.9 GHz Kryo 265 Silver) CPU which makes multi-tasking and playing video games easy and fun.\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>\r\\n<h5><strong>Increase Your Appetite with Dynamic Computing Engine:</strong></h5>\r\\nOppo A78 has 48-Month Fluency Protection. Say goodbye to lag, jitters, and jumps as Oppo’s proprietary technical solution delivers amazing fluidity and stability by keeping more apps active in the background.</li>\r\\n 	<li>\r\\n<h5><strong>Lab-tested Longevity</strong></h5>\r\\n: Say goodbye to lag, jitters, and jumps as OPPO’s proprietary technical solution delivers amazing fluidity and stability by keeping more apps active in the background.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Operating System</h3>\r\\nOppo A78 4G runs on Android 13, ColorOS 13.1. The Android-based operating system combines with Oppo’s ColorOS to optimize your experience and ability to customize applications to suit your needs, preferences, and personality.\r\\n<h3>Oppo A78 Battery Power and Performance</h3>\r\\nThe Li-Po 5000 mAh, non-removable battery is massive and its power capacity can last you 24 hours of intensive use, with some juice left for the following day.  The Battery Health Engine helps your battery remain good as new for over 4 years of daily use. It offers:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>3 Hours of YouTube streaming</li>\r\\n 	<li>293 Hours of offscreen standby</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n5 minutes of fast recharging using the 67W wired charger gives you ample 4.6 hours of making calls.  Within 46 minutes, your phone will be fully charged from 1-100%, getting ready for a run in the office or safari without any low power or slow charging inconveniences. Be ready in a flash with the 67W SUPERVOOC fast charging unit. Whether you have got to get to work, leave to collect the kids or meet your friends, you’ll not be left waiting with this ultra-fast flash charging, taking you to 43% in just 15 minutes and 76% in 30 minutes.\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Behaviour-Based Battery Charging Optimized All-Day Charging<strong>: </strong>If you leave your phone on charge for long periods, this super smartphone will reflect your routines, prompting you to switch on optimized all-day charging to protect your battery health. Your phone will charge to 80% then pause, restarting charging to get to full power just in time for when you need to leave.</li>\r\\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-A78','Oppo-A78',35000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(128,'Oppo A98','Oppo A98','Oppo-A98','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo A98','<h2>Oppo A98</h2>\r\