. Ergonomic design and is available in Gold, Black and Blue colours.\r\\n<h3>An Impressive and Immersive Display</h3>\r\\nThe Reno 10 features a 6.7-inch AMOLED, 1B colours, 120Hz, HDR10+, and 950 nits (peak) display.  Moreover, the thin bezels, at ~89.6% screen-to-body ratio, help maximise screen display and use space.\r\\n\r\\nWith 1080 x 2412 pixels and a 20:9 ratio (~394 ppi density) resolution, the Oppo phone has impressive and immersive resolutions for a mid-range smartphone. Additively, at ~394 ppi density resolution, 120Hz refresh rate, peak brightness at 950 nits, and ~89.6% screen-to-body ratio, the display on the Oppo Reno 10 is excellent for your immersive, cinematic user experience when playing games, watching videos, browsing the internet and social media interaction on Facebook, TikTok and Instagram.\r\\n\r\\nDespite having such highly rated display specifications, the screen is not protected by a Corning Gorilla protector, which is a let-down and oversight by Oppo, considering the unique nature of the display based on its specifications.\r\\n<h3>Decent Camera Set-up</h3>\r\\n<h4>Selfie Camera</h4>\r\\nThe front-facing camera features a 32 MP, f/2.4, 22mm (wide), 1/2.74″, 0.8µm, AF lens. At 32MP, you are assured of shooting great selfies of yourself, with family and with friends. Additionally, the selfie camera will enable you to record 1080p@30fps videos. Moreover, the gyro-EIS helps with video stabilization, which adds the quality of your video shots to high professional standards.\r\\n<h4>Main Camera</h4>\r\\nMounted at the rear of the phone is a triple camera set-up consisting of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>64 MP, f/1.7, (wide), 1/2″, 0.7µm, PDAF</li>\r\\n 	<li>32 MP, f/2.0, (telephoto), 1/2.74″, 0.8µm, PDAF, 2x optical zoom</li>\r\\n 	<li>8 MP, f/2.2, (ultrawide)</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe triple camera set-up will enable you to snap high-quality photos. Specifically, the 64MP (wide) camera will allow you to stitch multiple images into a high-quality one. With the 32MP (telephoto) lens, you can take pictures of things further away by zooming to take clear photos of your desired object. The 8MP ultrawide lens has a wide angle of view greater than 90°. It is ideally suited for capturing landscapes and pictures that require more scenery due to its ability to capture panoramic views and shots.\r\\n\r\\nFurther, the main camera features LED flash, HDR, and panorama, all offering various photo options based on your need and situation.\r\\n\r\\nFor video recording, the set camera will enable you to capture 4K@30fps and 1080p@30/60fps videos. The phone camera system supports gyro-EIS for stabilization and HDR for recorded videos.\r\\n<h3>A High-Performance Smartphone</h3>\r\\n<h4>Operating System</h4>\r\\nOppo Reno 10 runs on Android 13 OS. The latest Android OS version focuses on more user-facing features, increased security, themes, functions, privacy and productivity.\r\\n\r\\nMoreover, ColorOS 13.1 User Interface is Oppo’s latest UI, improving user experience. The updated UI comes along with the following:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Smart productivity</li>\r\\n 	<li>A fresh and aquamorphic design</li>\r\\n 	<li>Reliable experience</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nWith the newly upgraded OS and UI, you will have a unique, memorable experience that will make you fall in love and wholly connect to your Oppo Reno 10.\r\\n<h4>Processing Unit</h4>\r\\nThe handset is powered by Qualcomm SM7325 Snapdragon 778G 5G (6 nm) chipset. One of the essential attributes of the Snapdragon 778G chipset is the CPU and memory. Notably, the Snapdragon 778G Plus has more memory than the Snapdragon 860, which means faster app loading times and less lag time when using your phone.\r\\n\r\\nBesides, it also has an Octa-core processor (1×2.4 GHz Cortex-A78 &amp; 3×2.2 GHz Cortex-A78 &amp; 4×1.9 GHz Cortex-A55), which means it offers excellent performance when it comes to graphics and gaming.\r\\n\r\\nThe Snapdragon 778G 5G Mobile Platform brings premium smartphone experiences for gamers, including 5G gaming, Elite Gaming features, and all-day battery life. The Qualcomm Adreno 642L GPU offers up to 40% faster graphics rendering. And with a 6 nm process, this platform provides long-lasting interactions with remarkable efficiency.\r\\n<h4>Memory Space</h4>\r\\nOppo is packed with sufficient RAM and ROM to enable optimal smartphone use. Installed on the Oppo Reno 10 5G is the UFS 2.2 Technology on models with the following memory specifications:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>256GB 8GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>256GB 12GB RAM</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe Oppo Reno 10 model with 512GB internal and 12GB RAM uses UFS 3.1 technology to optimize memory space.\r\\n\r\\nUFS 2.2 and 3.1 technology offer better data transfer time (latency), which is 50% compared to Emmc. They offer lower power consumption. Thus, your Reno device’s battery life will be longer with such memory storage types.\r\\n\r\\nUFS 3.1 offers up to two times the data rate capabilities of UFS 2.2 (faster reading and writing capabilities) while lowering power consumption. UFS 3.1 is better than lesser versions like, in this case, UFS 2.2\r\\n\r\\nThe more RAM a phone has, the snappier its performance when switching between applications. Also, with more RAM, you can access and use applications that use much memory without adverse implications. This is true for Reno 10 5G, whose 12 GB RAM is remarkable. It allows it to run smoothly even when multiple applications open. Whereas other phones may stutter when running heavy applications such as heavy-setting games and video editors, the Oppo phone plays robustly due to its high RAM specifications.\r\\n\r\\nThe phone’s internal memory space specifications are commendable and sufficient. With up to 512GB of internal memory, such space is enough for storing hundreds of multimedia files and heavy documents without much of a problem. Rather than walking with a USB flash disk or HDD, you can use the smartphone’s internal storage to carry the needed files.\r\\n\r\\nThe phone does not support additional memory, with no MicroSD slot.\r\\n<h3>Network and Connectivity</h3>\r\\nOppo Reno 10 5G is a 5G-network-enabled smartphone. As a 5G handset, it will provide you with several benefits, including:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Increased bandwidth compared to 4G-enabled smartphone</li>\r\\n 	<li>Fast phone downloads over the network of movies, as well as enormous files and applications</li>\r\\n 	<li>Quick file uploads, such as video clip uploads to YouTube and TikTok, saving up loads of high-resolution photos</li>\r\\n 	<li>It combines blistering data speeds with almost zero lags to the network. This, in turn, enables video calls with pin-sharp resolution and minimal buffering</li>\r\\n 	<li>You will effortlessly streamline your video games in real time. It applies to high-definition gameplay and resource-heavy games such as PUBG Mobile.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Efficient Communication Systems</h3>\r\\nAs a modern-day 5G smartphone, Oppo Reno 10 5G is well equipped for the best communication and user experience. Oppo installed the latest WLAN (Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/6, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct) for faster internet connectivity and usability across a wide range of Wi-Fi Routers. You can match your handset to Wi-Fi Direct products, get connected and go to work or play. It is dual-band and works well within the 2.4 GHz to 5 GHz frequency bandwidth.\r\\n\r\\nThe phone supports NFC, which allows wireless data transmission over shorter distances using radio waves. With Near Field Communication technology (eSE, HCE, UICC, NFC-SIM), you can make more secure transactions, exchange digital content and connect with other NFC-supporting electronic devices with a touch.\r\\n\r\\nIt comes with the latest Bluetooth version, 5.2, A2DP, LE, aptX HD, enabling more accessibility and better connectivity with your BT devices such as Smart TV, headphones and ear pads. With the Advanced Audio Distribution Profile (A2DP), multi-media can be effortlessly streamed from your handset to other devices and vice-versa through Bluetooth Audio Streaming.\r\\n\r\\nOppo has adhered to its superior audio output mantra, especially for its mid-tier and high-end smartphones. Oppo Reno 10 5G comes packed with a loudspeaker for quality audio output, especially when the loudspeaker is turned on. Unfortunately, the phone lacks the 3.5mm jack port and radio, two components that, if you are old school and love both, will feel disconnected and missing something.\r\\n\r\\nOther features supported on the handset which ease communications and usage convenience include:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Infrared port</li>\r\\n 	<li>USB Type-C 2.0, OTG</li>\r\\n 	<li>Sensors: Fingerprint (under the display, optical), accelerometer, gyro, proximity, compass, colour spectrum</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nOppo Reno 10 5G is powered by a Li-Po 4,600 mAh, non-removable battery. Further, the battery can last 24 hours or a day of intensive usage thanks to the chipset that enables optimal battery power management and minimization of wastage.\r\\n\r\\nTo recharge the battery, you have an 80W wired, PD, QC3 fast charger capable of recharging 1- 50% of the battery in 11 min. Within 30 minutes, your battery is fully recharged and ready for maximum use.',NULL,NULL,'Oppo-Reno-10-5G','Oppo-Reno-10-5G',56000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(130,'Oppo Reno 10 Pro 5G','Oppo Reno 10 Pro 5G','Oppo-Reno-10-Pro-5G','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,4,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Oppo Reno 10 Pro 5G','<h2>Oppo Reno 10 Pro Specifications and Features</h2>\r\\n<h3>Physical Attributes of Reno 10 Pro</h3>\r\\nMassive. Elegant. Ergonomic design. Luxurious look. Outstanding aesthetics. Oppo Reno 10 Pro is a true gem, enclosed in a glass-fronted and backed body alongside a plastic frame. The glass enclosure is well-done to look glass-like and give the handset the undeniable premium look.  The aesthetics at the back complete the look at one of the most glamorous handsets ever developed by Op