 at the back features 64 MP (wide), 1/2″, PDAF, and 2 MP (depth) lenses, which capture high-quality pictures and 1080p@30/60fps videos.\r\\n<h3>The Operating and Processing Units</h3>\r\\nRealme C55 runs the Android 13 Operating System platform, complemented with Realme UI 4.0 for customization. It relies on a Mediatek Helio G88 (12nm) chipset for background operations, supported by an efficient Octa-core (2×2.0 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.8 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU and Mali-G52 MC2 GPU. The processing unit handles multi-tasking, playing low-setting games, and video streaming relatively well without stuttering and lagging.\r\\n<h3>Network and Communications</h3>\r\\nRealme C55 is a 4 G-enabled handset. It supports 2G, 3G, up to 4G bands, HSPA, and LTE-A network speed. Realme installed a loudspeaker and 3.5mm jack ports for the best communication while using the handset for convenient hands-free handling.  You have Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, and Bluetooth (5.2, A2DP, LE) options for wireless connectivity.\r\\n\r\\nYou can use Wi-Fi, USB Type-C 2.0, and NFC for fast data transfer. For accurate positioning and tracking, especially when traveling and out in the wild in an unfamiliar region, use the Global Positioning System (GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO, BDS) installed on the device.\r\\n\r\\nThe sensors installed on the handset include the following:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Fingerprint (side-mounted)</li>\r\\n 	<li>Accelerometer</li>\r\\n 	<li>Proximity sensor</li>\r\\n 	<li>compass</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Powering System</h3>\r\\nPowering the Realme C55 is a Li-Po 5000 mAh, non-removable battery. The massive battery gives at least two days of use if you are an average user. To recharge, use the fast 33W wired charger capable of restoring 1-50% of the battery in 29 minutes. Whether playing games or in a busy Schule that requires intensive phone use, the C55 battery and charging unit are up to the task.',NULL,NULL,'Realme-C55','Realme-C55',24000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(154,'Realme C55 - 128GB','Realme C55 - 128GB','Realme-C55-128GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,10,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Realme C55 - 128GB','Realme C55 - 128GB',NULL,NULL,'Realme-C55-128GB','Realme-C55-128GB',25500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(155,'Realme C55 - 256GB','Realme C55 - 256GB','Realme-C55-256GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,10,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Realme C55 - 256GB','Realme C55 - 256GB',NULL,NULL,'Realme-C55-256GB','Realme-C55-256GB',29500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(156,'Redmi 12','Redmi 12','Redmi-12','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,5,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Redmi 12','<h2>Redmi 12</h2>\r\\nThe Redmi 12 Price in Kenya is from Ksh 23,500 for the 128GB storage version. It comes running on a MediaTek Helio G88 Octacore processor with a RAM of 8GB. It has a 6.79 inch IPS LCD display with a refresh rate of 90Hz. The camera features 3 lenses, 50MP + 8MP + 2MP with a selfie camera of  8MP. Powered by a 5000 mAh battery you are guarantied a big battery with 18W charging speeds. The phone is available in a variant of Midnight Black, Sky Blue, and Polar Silver.\r\\n<h3>Design And Build</h3>\r\\nRedmi 12 weighs 198.5g and measures 168.6 x 76.3 x 8.2mm. It is not one of the slimmest or lightest handsets on the market, but its physical appearance and aesthetics make it attractive and functional to enable effective communication. The size is remarkable for easy handling with one hand, besides easy portability. It comes in beautiful colors: Midnight Black, Sky Blue, and Polar Silver. Notably, the Xiaomi handset is dust nor waterproof, with an IP53 rating.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nRedmi 12 boasts a 6.79-inch IPS LCD. The display has above average brightness of 550nits, besides the 1080 x 2460 pixels (~396 ppi density) resolution. 1080p resolution and 90Hz are good enough for a decent experience as you use the display for playing games, watching movies, and communicating with family and friends.\r\\n<h3>Camera Set-up</h3>\r\\nRedmi 12 packs an 8 MP, f/2.1, (wide) capable of recording 1080p@30fps. With the front-facing camera, you can capture decent selfie snapshots with family and friends. The main camera features a triple camera set-up at the handset’s rear. The lenses consist of the following:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>50 MP, f/1.8, (wide), PDAF</li>\r\\n 	<li>8 MP, f/2.2, 120˚ (ultrawide)</li>\r\\n 	<li>2 MP, f/2.4, (depth)</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nCombining the three lenses, bright quality, depth, and balance of light to capture images, thus improving the quality of pictures. Therefore, you can snap away and save memorable moments with workmates, friends, and family. The main camera captures 1080p@30fps videos.\r\\n<h3>Operating System &amp; Processing Unit</h3>\r\\nRedmi 12 runs on Android 13 OS, with the MIUI 14 software skin for optimal user interface. It is powered by an efficient Octa-core <a href=\"https://www.mediatek.com/products/smartphones-2/mediatek-helio-g88\">Mediatek Helio G88</a> (12nm) processor and a Mali-G52 MC2 GPU, making multitasking and mid-setting playing games on the handset smooth and enjoyable. Memory is vital to any device for optimal operation. The Redmi 12 packs sufficient inbuilt memory (128GB 4GB RAM, 128GB 8GB RAM, 256GB 8GB RAM) besides supporting additional memory (has a dedicated MicroSD slot).\r\\n<h3>Connectivity, Communication &amp; Sensors</h3>\r\\nRedmi 12 is 4G network enabled. The handset comes with A 3.5mm jack, supports FM radio, and is equipped with loudspeakers for music and loud communication in noisy places.  For motorists, the GPS (GPS, GLONASS, BDS, GALILEO) feature installed on the device is essential in that it helps in tracking and accurately pinpointing locations. It has several sensors for convenience when handling the device, including a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, accelerometer, and Virtual proximity sensing.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nRedmi 12 is powered by a powerful 5,000mAh battery, further supported by an 18W fast charger adding up to the convenience of using the handset.',NULL,NULL,'Redmi-12','Redmi-12',26000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(157,'Redmi 12 - 128GB','Redmi 12 - 128GB','Redmi-12-128GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,5,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Redmi 12 - 128GB','Redmi 12 - 128GB',NULL,NULL,'Redmi-12-128GB','Redmi-12-128GB',24000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(158,'Redmi 12 - 256GB','Redmi 12 - 256GB','Redmi-12-256GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,5,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Redmi 12 - 256GB','Redmi 12 - 256GB',NULL,NULL,'Redmi-12-256GB','Redmi-12-256GB',26000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(159,'Redmi A2 Plus','Redmi A2 Plus','Redmi-A2-Plus','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,5,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Redmi A2 Plus','<h2>Redmi A2 Plus Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Design, Body Build, and Display</h3>\r\\nXiaomi Redmi A2 Plus measures 164.9 x 76.8 x 9.1 mm and weighs 196g. The device’s body is made of plastic at the back, with a plastic body frame and glass front. The 6.52-inch display of the Xiaomi handset is made of IPS LCD with a 60Hz refresh rate and a 720 x 1600 pixels resolution (~ 269 ppi density). This is enough for using your new device for both work and play.\r\\n<h3>Performance and Battery</h3>\r\\nThe handset features Octa-core (4×2.2 GHz Cortex-A53 &amp; 4×1.7 GHz Cortex-A53) (CPU), Mediatek Helio G36 (12 nm) chipset, and PowerVR GE8320 GPU running on the Android 12 (Go edition) OS, with MIUI for customizations. The processor is powerful enough for multi-tasking and playing basic games. The 32GB 2GB RAM / 32GB 3GB RAM internal memory space is sufficient to run basic applications, and some preferred downloaded applications. You can expand the space using the MicroSD option up to 512GB. A 5,000mAh Li-Po non-removable battery powers the device. A 10W fast charger enables quick powering of the storm.\r\\n<h3>Redmi A2 Plus Camera</h3>\r\\nYou can take average selfie shots and videos on the front-facing 5MP camera. At the back, the device packs a dual camera set-up of 8MP +0