iencing lags and stuttering.\r\\n\r\\nEqually, enabling seamless operations is abundant RAM and ROM installed on the handset. Has inbuilt memory  of 256GB 8GB RAM. It supports MicroSD is supported, which is a significant consideration to support internal memory and offer unlimited memory space for multimedia files, documents, and downloadable applications.\r\\n<h3>Network and Communications</h3>\r\\nAnother great complement that makes Redmi Note 12S worth owing in 2023 is its network connectivity. It is 4G enabled and supports up to 4G networks, depending on your network supplier and coverage in your area. With 4G, the user is assured of fast uploading and downloading of content and data. 5G would be just as great, but for that option, you must opt for Xiaomi Note 12 Pro and Redmi Note 12 5G. Several sensors are installed on the handset, which enables convenience when communicating and handling the device.\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Fingerprint (side-mounted) sensor</li>\r\\n 	<li>Accelerometer</li>\r\\n 	<li>Gyroscope</li>\r\\n 	<li>Proximity sensor</li>\r\\n 	<li>Compass</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Redmi Note 12S Battery</h3>\r\\nA Li-Po 5,000 mAh, non-removable battery powers the Note 12S. A fast 33W charger enabled fast charge of the battery. Depending on your usage intensity, you are assured of 2 days of charge, with the fast charger handy for charging on the go.\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3293\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3293\" aria-labelledby=\"tablepress-3293-name\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Xiaomi</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Redmi Note 12S</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-4\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Announced</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">2023, March 06</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-5\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Released</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>April 2023</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-6\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Operating System</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Android 13, MIUI 14</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-7\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Chipset</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Mediatek Helio G96 (12 nm)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-8\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>CPU Speed</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Octa-core (2×2.05 GHz Cortex-A76 &amp; 6×2.0 GHz Cortex-A55)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-9\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPU</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Mali-G57 MC2</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-10\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Storage</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>256GB</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-11\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>RAM</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>8GB</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-12\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Card Slot</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>microSDXC (uses shared SIM slot)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-13\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Rear Camera</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>108 MP + 8 MP + 2 MP</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-14\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Front Camera</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">12 MP</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-15\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Network</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>GSM / HSPA / LTE / 5G</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-16\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sim Card</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Hybrid Dual SIM (Nano-SIM, dual stand-by)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-17\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Weight</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>188 g (6.63 oz)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-18