ery</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Li-Po 5000 mAh, non-removable</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-29\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Fast Charging</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>25W wired</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>\r\\n<h3>Physical Attributes</h3>\r\\nThe Galaxy A34 is framed in simple lines and a plastic finish, Galaxy A34 5G is available in fashionable yet timeless colors, including Awesome Lime, Awesome Silver, Awesome Violet, and Awesome Graphite. Measuring 161.3 x 78.1 x 8.2 mm and weighing 199g, the Samsung phone is as massive as it is weighty. Made of the front glass, plastic frame, and plastic back pane, the phone feels light and comfortable to handle your grasp or pocket. The fact that the handset has a dual SIM card slot and is IP67 dust/water resistant (up to 1m for 30 min) makes it functional and great for optimal use without worries of water splashes, screen breaking, or lack of network.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nGalaxy A34 5G’s 1,000nits, Super AMOLED, 6.6-inch display ensures a clear view even when outside. Enjoy silky smooth viewing on the 6.6-inch excellent screen and refresh rates of up to 120Hz that breathe life into your content. Protecting the 1080 x 2340 pixels (~390 ppi density) resolution screen is a Corning Gorilla Glass.\r\\n<h3>Camera Set-up</h3>\r\\nThe main camera consists of a triple-camera setup:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>48 MP, f/1.8, 26mm (wide), 1/2.0″, 0.8µm, PDAF, OIS</li>\r\\n 	<li>8 MP, f/2.2, 123˚, (ultrawide), 1/4.0″, 1.12µm</li>\r\\n 	<li>5 MP, f/2.4, (macro)</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe primary camera can record 4K@30fps, 1080p@30/60fps, and 720p@480fps videos. For selfies, capture moments with the decent 13 MP, f/2.2, (wide), 1/3.1″, 1.12µm camera. The camera equally captures 4K videos. Galaxy A34 5G records your finest moments in bright, vivid colors, even in the dark, and adjusts the frame to fit the group perfectly with Auto Framing. Perfect your shots with Photo Remaster. Reduce blur and noise while increasing the resolution of your photos with an intuitive, AI-powered tool. You do not need to wait for that perfect shot. Take the picture and edit out unwanted objects, shadows, reflections, and more with the Object Eraser.\r\\n<h3>Processing Power</h3>\r\\nPowering the handset is a decent MediaTek MT6877V Dimensity 1080 (6 nm) chipset, enabling efficient operations on the device and optimal battery use. Along with the CPU comes a reliable Octa-core (2×2.6 GHz Cortex-A78 &amp; 6×2.0 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU and Mali-G68 MC4, both of which make it possible to multi-task, browse through multiple pages, play low to mid-level setting games and stream videos. The handset runs on Android’s latest V13 OS, supported with One UI 5.1\r\\n<h3>Memory Space</h3>\r\\nThe handset comes installed with an internal memory of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>128GB 6GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>128GB 8GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>256GB 8GB RAM</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe RAM and ROM are sufficient for basic and advanced phone use, especially for high-performance tasks requiring good RAM and applications that demand adequate memory. Besides, the handset supports additional memory with microSDXC (uses a shared SIM slot).\r\\n<h3>Network &amp; Communications</h3>\r\\nSamsung Galaxy A34 is 5G enabled. With a 5G network, you will enjoy fast loading and downloading of videos and large files, which take longer on lesser networks. Supporting the device are:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Latest 5.3, A2DP, LE for wireless connectivity</li>\r\\n 	<li>GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO, BDS</li>\r\\n 	<li>Stereo speakers for better audibility when listening to music and streaming videos</li>\r\\n 	<li>Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct</li>\r\\n 	<li>Supports NFC for data transfer</li>\r\\n 	<li>USB Type-C 2.0, OTG</li>\r\\n 	<li>Fingerprint (under display, optical), accelerometer, gyro, compass, and Virtual proximity sensing.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nUnfortunately, the device does not support FM Radio 3.5mm jack port. It would be best to get used to Bluetooth pairing and Wi-Fi for audio-visual content consumption.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nPowering the Galaxy A34 is a 5,000mAh battery, recharged by a wired, fast 25W charger.',NULL,NULL,'Samsung-Galaxy-A34-5G','Samsung-Galaxy-A34-5G',52500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(196,'Samsung Galaxy A54 5G','Samsung Galaxy A54 5G','Samsung-Galaxy-A54-5G','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,2,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Samsung Galaxy A54 5G','<h2>Samsung Galaxy A54 5G specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\nThe Samsung Galaxy A54 5G has a minimalist design and build but still stands out as a mid-tier smartphone. Its smoothened round edges and thin frame characteristically help define it, besides the 8.2mm thickness. It is undoubtedly a massive and heavy phone, going by its weight and thickness (206g weight, 8.2mm). The device comes in various colors giving you options on what best represents your style and vibe. The colors available are Lime, Graphite, Violet, and White. While a large 6.4-inch button-holed display dominates the front, the back has a slight protrusion to accommodate the main camera setup. Samsung Galaxy smartphones consistently achieve a luxury status, and the A54 5G is quite luxurious and elegant to match its friendly price tag.\r\\n<h3>Samsung Galaxy A54 5G Display</h3>\r\\nA dominant 6.4-inch PLS LCD with a refresh rate of 120Hz will catch your eye the first time you get hold of the Samsung Galaxy A54 5G device.  The Super AMOLED display with 1080 x 2340 pixels (403ppi) is impressive and immersive, giving you a cinematic experience as you consume your content, work, and socialize. A 120Hz refresh rate ensures peak performance without lagging and stuttering as it takes the device through its paces.  Protecting the immersive display is a tamper-proof Corning Gorilla 5 Glass.\r\\n<h3>Network Connectivity</h3>\r\\nThe Samsung Galaxy A54 5G supports up to 5G Network Connectivity. It means faster data download, upload speeds, and connection when communicating on the network.\r\\n<h3>Camera</h3>\r\\nThe device has a high-performing Samsung Galaxy A54 5G triple main camera system. The main camera system at the device’s rear comprises a triple set:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>50 MP, f/1.8, (wide), PDAF</li>\r\\n 	<li>12 MP, f/2.2, 123˚ (ultrawide), 1.12µm</li>\r\\n 	<li>5 MP, f/2.4, (macro)</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe width and depth cameras enable high-quality capture and images and videos, balancing light, brightness, ambiance, and softness while eliminating noise for more clarity. The primary camera captures up to 4K videos, hence. At the front, the Samsung Galaxy A54 5G packs a 32 MP, f/2.2, 26mm (wide), 1/2.8″, 0.8µm camera that captures 4K videos. You will not miss great moments with family and friends or alone as you travel and explore the world.\r\\n<h3>Performance</h3>\r\\n<strong>Memory Space:</strong> The device comes with 6/8GB RAM (depending on model), which is significant for the smooth running of numerous pre-installed applications and other essential downloads. The internal memory of 128/256GB complements the relatively large RAM, besides the additional external addition of memory (optional, up to 1 TB). You are thus at liberty to download and install as many apps as possible, besides multi-media files, for your indulgence.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Processing Power:</strong> A powerful Octa-core Octa-core (4×2.4 GHz Cortex-A78 &amp; 4×2.0 GHz Cortex-A55) processor keeps the device going without lagging or stuttering, whether you are multi-tasking, live streaming videos, or playing their favorite mobile video. Running on the latest Android platform, Android 13 OS, the Samsung Galaxy integrated its One User Interface (One UI 5) to enable users to customize and optimize their experience with the device. Mali-G68 MP5 GPU, paired with Exynos 1380 (5nm) chipset, ensures optimal video game performance. Both validate the Samsung Galaxy M54 5G as a powerful mid-tier smartphone to own and use.\r\\n<h2>Battery</h2>\r\\nA powerful 5,000 mAh non-removable battery powers the Samsung Galaxy A54 5G. The battery adequately meets the demands of the large phone. A fast charger of 25W enables rapid charging of the storm, hence the assurance of quick charging on the go.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3369\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3369\" aria-labelledby=\"tablepress-3369-name\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Samsung</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Samsung Galaxy A54</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-4\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Announced</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>March 2023</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-5\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Released</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>March 2023</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-6\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Operating System</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Android 13, One UI 5.1</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-7\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Chipset</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Exynos 1380 (5 nm)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-8\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>CPU Speed</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Octa-core (4×2.4 GHz Cortex-A78 &amp; 4×2.0 GHz Cortex-A55)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-9\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPU Graphics Processor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Mali-G68 MP5</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-10\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Storage</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>128GB/256GB</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-11\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>RAM</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>6GB/8GB</div