xy S22 5G','Samsung Galaxy S22 5G','Samsung-Galaxy-S22-5G','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,2,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Samsung Galaxy S22 5G','<div class=\"electro-description clearfix\"><h2>Samsung Galaxy S22 5G</h2><p>The Samsung Galaxy S22 5G price in Kenya starts at Ksh 101',NULL,NULL,'Samsung-Galaxy-S22-5G','Samsung-Galaxy-S22-5G',105999,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(200,'Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra 5G','Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra 5G','Samsung-Galaxy-S22-Ultra-5G','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,2,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra 5G','<div class=\"electro-description clearfix\"><h2>Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra 5G</h2><p>The Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra price in Kenya starts at 132',NULL,NULL,'Samsung-Galaxy-S22-Ultra-5G','Samsung-Galaxy-S22-Ultra-5G',159999,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(201,'Samsung Galaxy S23 5G','Samsung Galaxy S23 5G','Samsung-Galaxy-S23-5G','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,2,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Samsung Galaxy S23 5G','<h2>Samsung Galaxy S23 5G Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h4>Design</h4>\r\\nSamsung Galaxy S23 5G ergonomic design is inspired by nature. The selection of colors (Phantom Black, Cream, Green, Lavender, Graphite, and Lime) are all down-to-earth tones. The fresh new colors are inspired by nature and made with natural dyes and infused into the polished metal frame. With earth in mind, each part of the S23 is rafted with recycled glass and ocean-bound plastic, and each phone is packaged in a box made of recycled materials.\r\\n<h4>Samsung Galaxy S23 5G Build</h4>\r\\nBy build, Samsung Galaxy S23 is made of a Glass front (Gorilla Glass Victus 2), glass back (Gorilla Glass Victus 2), and aluminum frame. An Armor aluminum frame with tougher drop and scratch resistance makes the handset premium, and resistant to breakage and scratches.\r\\n\r\\nIt measures 146.3 x 70.9 x 7.6 mm and weighs 168g. considerably, it is featherlight and slim, great characteristics which define the premium device and make it stand out from other handsets. It supports Nano-SIM and eSIM or Dual SIM (2 Nano-SIMs and eSIM, dual stand-by. The device is IP68 rated (dust/water resistant) up to 1.5m of water for 30 mins.\r\\n<h4>Display</h4>\r\\nGame or stream anywhere with adaptive visibility delivering optimal color and brightness, in any light. Adaptive 120Hz smooths the scroll, while Eye Comfort Shield keeps your eyes from getting tired, even as you view in the dark. Featuring a 6.1-inch Dynamic AMOLED 2X display, Samsung Galaxy S23 is creative for immersion and high performance. With up to 1750 nits peak brightness and 1080 x 2340 pixels, 19.5:9 ratio (~422 ppi density) resolution, be assured of great cinematic experiences when browsing the internet and enjoying video content. Protecting the awesome display is a tamper-proof, Corning Gorilla Glass Victus 2 (Corning Gorilla Glass Victus 2).\r\\n<h4>High Performance, Based on Superior Processing Power</h4>\r\\nRunning on Android 13 OS, Samsung Galaxy S23 5G provides you with the latest and upgraded apps to optimize your utility and productivity. To enhance the user experience, it comes installed with One UI 5.1 app software skin that makes customization and personalization possible. Now it’s easier than ever to set your phone up just for you. One UI maximizes customization, allowing you to pick almost every detail, including video lock screens and custom widgets. Powering the S23 is the uncompromising, high-performance, Qualcomm SM8550-AC Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 (4 nm) chipset.\r\\n\r\\nWhen combined with Octa-core (1×3.36 GHz Cortex-X3 &amp; 2×2.8 GHz Cortex-A715 &amp; 2×2.8 GHz Cortex-A710 &amp; 3×2.0 GHz Cortex-A510) CPU and Adreno 740, Samsung Galaxy S23 is well equipped for:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Efficiency in battery use and management when gaming or in an intensive work session</li>\r\\n 	<li>Minimization of lagging and stuttering</li>\r\\n 	<li>High response when multi-tasking</li>\r\\n 	<li>Great gaming experience for high-setting games.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h4>Memory Specification</h4>\r\\nThe premium handset comes equipped with sufficient inbuilt memory for downloading apps and storing multimedia. It consists of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>128GB 8GB RAM, UFS 3.1</li>\r\\n 	<li>256GB 8GB RAM, UFS 3.1</li>\r\\n 	<li>512GB 8GB RAM</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nIt is important to note that the Galaxy smartphone does not support additional memory, with no MicroSD slot.\r\\n<h4>Camera</h4>\r\\n<h4>Selfie Camera</h4>\r\\nShoot your shots with the cameras installed on the Samsung Galaxy S23. The 12MP front camera (12 MP, f/2.2, 26mm (wide), Dual Pixel PDAF) has Dual video call, Auto-HDR, and HDR10+ features making it one of the best selfie cameras in 2023 among premium handsets.\r\\n\r\\nThe Front Camera’s Dual Pixel technology focuses faster, even in low light. Object-based AI delivers authentic colours for selfies that rival real life.\r\\n\r\\nThe impressive camera is equally capable of 4K@30/60fps, and 1080p@30fps video recordings. Don’t just capture the dark with stills. Get pin-sharp night videos, too. Now, even the front Selfie Camera has the skills to capture clips of you and your friends after the sun sets.\r\\n<h4>The main camera</h4>\r\\nSeize the day and capture the night. Head out with a camera that’s equipped with a high-resolution sensor and intelligent, light-absorbing pixels — delivering clear pics at any hour. Get ready for a Gallery full of epic night shots everyone will want. Nightography’s enhanced AI keeps details clear, so low-light photos and videos stay bright and colorful, from dusk to dawn.\r\\n\r\\nThe main camera features a triple camera set-up consisting of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>50 MP, f/1.8, 24mm (wide), 1/1.56″, 1.0µm, Dual Pixel PDAF, OIS</li>\r\\n 	<li>10 MP, f/2.4, 70mm (telephoto), 1/3.94″, 1.0µm, PDAF, 3x optical zoom</li>\r\\n 	<li>12 MP, f/2.2, 13mm, 120˚ (ultrawide), 1/2.55″ 1.4µm, Super Steady video</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe 50MP Wide-Angle Camera works hand-in-hand with a powerful processor, rapidly combining frames to extract bits from each into a single hi-res photo. Add in Detail Enhancer technology and you’ve got quality so sharp; you’ll keep zooming in for more. Shoot hi-res RAW images for bright and detailed shots ready for pro-level editing. Then look to the stars as the camera pulls in light to capture constellations with breathtaking clarity.\r\\n\r\\nHead to the Gallery to enhance dark, blurry images and even upscale low-res photos. You can also revamp fuzzy GIFs, reducing noise and upping clarity to keep your loops looking fresh. Record high-quality videos using the triple camera set-up that can capture 8K@24/30fps, 4K@30/60fps, 1080p@30/60/240fps, 720p@960fps, HDR10+, alongside stereo sound recording with gyro-EIS.\r\\n<h4>Excellent Communication Features and Support</h4>\r\\nThe handset boasts an impressive array of features that aid in optimizing communication as you use it. Connectivity is enabled through WLAN (Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/6e, tri-band, Wi-Fi Direct), making it possible for you to fully enjoy the Samsung Galaxy S23 when you have access to reliable internet.\r\\n\r\\nGo ahead and pair the handset with your devices via Bluetooth. Whether on your morning run, driving to work, or at home seeking some cool entertainment you can seamlessly connect your handset to your smartphone, buds, music system or QLED Smart TV and awesomely enjoy the experience. While traveling or out for adventure, make use of the positioning feature (GPS, GLONASS, BDS, GALILEO) for accurate location, positioning, and tracking in case you get lost in unfamiliar terrain.\r\\n\r\\nThe stereo loudspeakers make Samsung Galaxy S23 an awesome device to own for self-indulgence, with the loud, high-quality sound output unmistakable. If you are streaming a movie or simply listening to your favorite music hits, the stereo loudspeakers will get you right in the groove. As expected, the S23 like its predecessor the S22 does not support FM Radio and has no 3.5mm jack. To listen to audio output, you need to connect via Bluetooth on your listening devices. It is great to note that the handset supports NFC AND OTG, via its USB Type-C 3.2 port.\r\\n<h4>Network</h4>\r\\nSamsung Galaxy S23 IS 5G-network enabled. It relies on GSM / CDMA / HSPA / EVDO / LTE / 5G network technology and supports 2G, 3G, 4G, and 5G bands. Running up to HSPA, LTE, and 5G network speed, you can be sure of enjoying fast, uncompromised uploading and downloading of large files, movies, and multi-media.\r\\n<h4>Battery</h4>\r\\nPowering the S23 is a 3,900mAh battery. To enable continued, uninterrupted gaming and use of the handset, it comes along with a 25W wired fast charger capable of recharging 1-50% of the battery in 30 minutes. The charging system also supports wireless charging (Qi/PMA) and 4.5W reverse wireless charging.\r\\n<h4>Pros and Cons</h4>\r\\n<h4>Pros</h4>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Drop and scratch resistance.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Sufficient inbuilt memory</li>\r\\n 	<li>5G enabled</li>\r\\n 	<li>Superior display: Dynamic AMOLED 2x display with 120Hz refresh rate support.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Tamper-proof Corning Gorilla Glass Victus 2 screen protector</li>\r\\n 	<li>IP68 dust and water resistance rating.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Upto 8K Video Recording.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Gyro-EIS support</li>\r\\n 	<li>Android 13 OS with One UI 5.1 custom UI.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Flagship-level chipset performance.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Ultrawide and Optical zoom cameras are present.</li>\r\\n 	<li>25W fast charging support.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Wireless and 4.5W reverse wireless charging support.</li>\r\\n 	<li>It comes with Samsung Dex and Wireless Dex support.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h4>Cons</h4>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Low battery capacity for such a premium phone</li>\r\\n 	<li>Does not support MicroSD</li>\r\\n 	<li>Low battery backup support</li>\r\\n 	<li>No 3.5mm jack</li>\r\\n 	<li>Without a micro-SD card slot.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3315\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3315\" aria-labelledby=\"tablepress-3315