/img.png',0,2,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Samsung Galaxy S23 Plus 5G','<h2>Samsung Galaxy S23 Plus 5G Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Design</h3>\r\\nNicely rounded edges and curved edges define the ergonomic design of the Samsung Galaxy S23 Plus 5G. Samsung focused on a minimalist, premium design that oozes class and elegance in the S23+ model.\r\\n<h3>Samsung Galaxy S23 Plus 5G Build</h3>\r\\nThe handset measures 157.8 x 76.2 x 7.6 mm. it weighs 196g. note the slim design, which when combined with weight and fit in the hand makes the Galaxy S23+ comfortable to carry around and handle with one hand. The device is made of Glass front (Gorilla Glass Victus 2), glass back (Gorilla Glass Victus 2), and aluminum frame. The phone supports Nano-SIM and eSIM or Dual SIM (2 Nano-SIMs and eSIM, dual stand-by). Protecting the expensively assembled Galaxy S23+ is an Armor aluminum frame with tougher drop and scratch resistance. Important to note too is the fact that the handset is IP68 dust/water resistant (up to 1.5m for 30 mins).\r\\n<h3>Samsung Galaxy S23 Plus 5G Display</h3>\r\\nA 6.6-inch Dynamic AMOLED 2X, 120Hz, HDR10+, 1750 nits (peak) display dominates the Samsung Galaxy S23+. Once powered on, you will have no dull moment as you delve into the cinematic display that will have you wanting to explore the applications and phone features. An 87.6% screen-to-body ratio and thin bezels help maximize display space for use. 1080 x 2340 pixels, 19.5:9 ratio (~393 ppi density) coupled with 1,750 nits peak brightness makes the S23+ one of the best screens on Samsung handsets for optimal user experience. An under-display, ultra-sonic fingerprint sensor provides enhanced security on the handset to prevent unauthorized access. Protecting the impressive, Dynamic AMOLED 2X display is a tamper-proof Corning Gorilla Glass Victus 2.\r\\n<h3>Camera set-up</h3>\r\\nThe main camera on the Samsung Galaxy S23 Plus 5G consists of t a triple setup:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li><em>50 MP, f/1.8, 24mm (wide), 1/1.56″, 1.0µm, Dual Pixel PDAF, OIS</em></li>\r\\n 	<li><em>10 MP, f/2.4, 70mm (telephoto), 1/3.94″, 1.0µm, PDAF, OIS, 3x optical zoom</em></li>\r\\n 	<li><em>12 MP, f/2.2, 13mm, 120˚ (ultrawide), 1/2.55″ 1.4µm, Super Steady video</em></li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nIt is capable of taking up to 8K Video recordings, with optical 3x Zoom, gyro-EIS, LED Flash, and Super Steady video key features which enable superior performance. The selfie camera consists of a 12 MP, f/2.2, 26mm (wide), Dual Pixel PDAF lens, with\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Dual video call capabilities</li>\r\\n 	<li>Auto-HDR</li>\r\\n 	<li>HDR10+</li>\r\\n 	<li>4K@30/60fps, 1080p@30fps video recording capabilities.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nBoth the front and main cameras intelligently recognize scenes and optimize colors for brilliant shots.\r\\n<h3>Operating System and Phone Processing Unit</h3>\r\\nRunning in the background is Android 13 OS, with the One UI 5.1 skin enabling customization and personalization of the handset. To enable optimal operations on the handset, the S23+ is equipped with a:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Powerful Qualcomm SM8550-AC Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 (4 nm) chipset</li>\r\\n 	<li>Efficient Octa-core (1×3.36 GHz Cortex-X3 &amp; 2×2.8 GHz Cortex-A715 &amp; 2×2.8 GHz Cortex-A710 &amp; 3×2.0 GHz Cortex-A510) CPU than enables smooth operations when multi-tasking, browsing through multiple web pages and applications.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Proficient Adreno 740 GPU that enables playing games with high settings.</li>\r\\n 	<li>256GB / 512GB ROM, 8GB RAM, with UFS 4.0 for memory space optimization.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Network and Communications set-up</h3>\r\\nSamsung Galaxy S23+ is 5G enabled, supporting up to 5G bands (2G, 3G, 4G and 5G). With 5G network connectivity, you can upload and download heavy files and multimedia in record time. The handset has a range of sensors for convenient handling and communications. They include:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Fingerprint (under the display, ultrasonic)</li>\r\\n 	<li>Accelerometer</li>\r\\n 	<li>Gyro</li>\r\\n 	<li>Proximity</li>\r\\n 	<li>Compass</li>\r\\n 	<li>Barometer</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe device supports Wi-Fi, Bluetooth connectivity, GPS, NFC and has USB Type-C 3.2, OTG for fast data transfer to or from other devices with USB ports.\r\\n<h3>Powering System</h3>\r\\nPowering the handset is a 4,700mAh non-removable battery. The powering system consists of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>45W wired, PD3.0, 65% in 30 min</li>\r\\n 	<li>15W wireless (Qi/PMA)</li>\r\\n 	<li>5W reverse wireless</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>PROS AND CONS OF SAMSUNG GALAXY S23+</h3>\r\\n<h3>Pros</h3>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Armor aluminum frame for drop and scratch resistance.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Dynamic AMOLED 2x display with 120Hz refresh rate support.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Comes with Corning Gorilla Glass Victus 2</li>\r\\n 	<li>Large battery at 4,700mAh</li>\r\\n 	<li>Slim phone at 7.6 mm thickness</li>\r\\n 	<li>Supports 45W fast charging</li>\r\\n 	<li>Supports 4.5W reverse charging</li>\r\\n 	<li>Supports wireless charging</li>\r\\n 	<li>Supports S-Pen</li>\r\\n 	<li>IP68 rating (water and dustproof)</li>\r\\n 	<li>Also comes with stylus pen support.</li>\r\\n 	<li>The latest Android 13 OS with One UI 5.1 custom UI.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Powerful chipset ideal for high-setting games</li>\r\\n 	<li>Cameras intelligently recognize scenes and optimize colours for brilliant shots.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Capable of 8K video recordings with HDR10+ gyro-EIS support.</li>\r\\n 	<li>3x and 10x Optical zoom cameras installed</li>\r\\n 	<li>Samsung Dex and Wireless Dex support.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Has Gyro-EIS and Super Steady video support</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Cons</h3>\r\\n<ol>\r\\n 	<li>It does not support MicroSD (additional memory)</li>\r\\n 	<li>No 3.5mm jack</li>\r\\n 	<li>S-Pen bought separately.</li>\r\\n 	<li>Bulky and heavy phone</li>\r\\n 	<li>Priced out for most buyers at its current retail price</li>\r\\n</ol>\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3316\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3316\" aria-labelledby=\"tablep