\">\r\\n<div>Weight</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">187 g (6.60 oz)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-18\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Dimensions</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Unfolded: 165.2 x 71.9 x 6.9 mm\r\\nFolded: 84.9 x 71.9 x 15.9-17.1 mm</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-19\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Screen Resolution</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>1080 x 2640 pixels (~426 ppi density)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-20\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Type</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Foldable Dynamic AMOLED 2X, 120Hz, HDR10+, 1200 nits (peak)\r\\nCover display: Super AMOLED</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-21\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Size</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>6.7 inches, 101.5 cm2 (~85.4% screen-to-body ratio)\r\\nCover display: 1.9 inches, 260 x 512 pixels (Gorilla Glass Victus+)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-22\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>3.5mm jack</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>No\r\\n32-bit/384kHz audio\r\\nTuned by AKG</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-23\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Bluetooth</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>5.1, A2DP, LE</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-24\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPS</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>A-GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO, BDS</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-25\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>NFC</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Yes</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-26\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/6, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-27\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>USB</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>USB Type-C 2.0, USB On-The-Go</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-28\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Radio</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>No</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-29\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sensor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Fingerprint (side-mounted), accelerometer, gyro, proximity, compass, barometer\r\\nSamsung Pay (Visa, MasterCard certified)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-30\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Battery</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Li-Po 3700 mAh, non-removable</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-31\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Fast Charging</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Fast charging 25W\r\\nFast wireless charging 10W\r\\nReverse wireless charging 4.5W</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Flip4','Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Flip4',99999,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(215,'Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5','Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5','Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Fold-5','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,2,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5','<h2>Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 5 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Design and Build</h3>\r\\nGo Big and Relive every moment with the massive, premium, and elegant Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5. Samsung has trimmed down the design, so you can stay close to the things you love without sacrificing an ounce of power. The smartphone measures 154.9 x 67.1 x 13.4 mm when folded and 154.9 x 129.9 x 6.1 mm (unfolded). Fold5 weighs 253g.\r\\n\r\\nWith five shades to choose from, Galaxy Z Fold5 makes a statement and shows off your unique style,  including exclusive colors: Icy Blue, Phantom Black, Cream, Gray, and Blue. The laws of physics have nothing on this leveled-up design. Galaxy Z Fold5 lives up to its name by folding closed, making a massive screen implausibly pocketable. Open it up, fold it shut or flex it to the perfect angle. The redesigned Flex Hinge is a technical marvel that bends to your will.\r\\n\r\\nThe Fold5 is made of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Glass front (Gorilla Glass Victus 2) (folded)</li>\r\\n 	<li>plastic front (unfolded)</li>\r\\n 	<li>glass back (Gorilla Glass Victus 2),</li>\r\\n 	<li>aluminum frame.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe Armor aluminum frame comes along with tougher drop and scratch resistance. The frame supports Stylus Pen. It is water and dust resistant, with an IPX8 rating (up to 1.5m for 30 min).\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nThe Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5 Unfold more with an expansive screen and immerse yourself in your favorite entertainment no matter where you are with Galaxy Z Fold5. Unfold a stunning, immersive 7.6″ screen reimagined to bring you gaming like never before, cinematic viewing, and improved productivity. Enjoy a movie-going experience on the bright 7.6″ Main Screen without direct sunlight ruining the view.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Multiple Apps, One Screen</strong>: Multi-Window View takes your multitasking to the next level. Keep three windows open on one screen, so you can stream, shop, browse, and play more. The taskbar holds up to twelve apps at once so you can effortlessly swap between your favorites.\r\\n<h3>Stylus Pen</h3>\r\\nThe big screen when unfolded meets the velvet smoothness and precision of the stylus pen. Precision meets portability with the Galaxy Z Fold5 S Pen. Write directly on the large screen and go from to-do to done. Plus, use Samsung Notes for a canvas that syncs across Galaxy devices. The Slim S Pen Case makes it easy to carry the S Pen around with your phone and for on-the-go precision.\r\\n\r\\nGood Notes give you the opportunity for more control. Massive Productivity for Work: Samsung’s slimmest, most durable Fold yet boasts a massive 7.6” screen† that opens to elevate productivity on the go. Multitask with Dual-App viewing and increased S Pen precision.\r\\n<h3>Samsung Galaxy Z Fold5 Assurance</h3>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li><strong>Cutting edge Innovation: </strong>5th Gen foldable technology utilizing advanced, time-tested folding innovation.</li>\r\\n 	<li><strong>Built to Withstand:</strong> the Fold5 is tested and verified to withstand 200,000 folds over 5 years of daily use.\r\\nFeaturing the zero-gap Flex Hinge, Gorilla Glass Victus 2, and IPX8 water resistance.</li>\r\\n 	<li><strong>Out-of-the-Box Screen Protection:</strong> Internal screen protection is pre-installed on Galaxy Z products. Plus get a free one-time screen protector replacement if needed.</li>\r\\n 	<li><strong>Worry-Free Screen Protection: </strong>Get special coverage for a discounted, one-time screen replacement due to a defect or accident.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Camera set up</h3>\r\\nAs expected, the cameras installed on the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold5 stand out, based on their superior performance.\r\\n<h3>Selfies</h3>\r\\ncapture selfies with:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>4 MP, f/1.8, 26mm (wide), 2.0µm, under display</li>\r\\n 	<li>10 MP, f/2.2, 24mm (wide), 1/3″, 1.22µm Cover Camera</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe cover camera is capable to record 4K@30/60fps, and 1080p@30/60fps videos, supported by Gyro-EIS for image stabilization.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Preview Pictures from the Cover Screen</strong>: Whether behind the camera or in front of it, see your pose in the viewfinder with Dual Preview.\r\\n<h3>Main Camera</h3>\r\\n<strong>T</strong>he main camera consists of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>50 MP, f/1.8, 23mm (wide), 1.0µm, Dual Pixel PDAF, OIS</li>\r\\n 	<li>10 MP, f/2.4, (telephoto), PDAF, OIS, 3x optical zoom</li>\r\\n 	<li>12 MP, f/2.2, 123˚, 12mm (ultrawide), 1.12µm</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe triple camera setup combines to capture high-quality snapshots. LED flash, HDR, and panorama features give you options on what shots to take depending on timing and preference without compromising on the quality of your pictures.\r\\n\r\\nFor videos, you can record 8K@24fps, 4K@60fps, 1080p@60/240fps (gyro-EIS), 720p@960fps (gyro-EIS), HDR10+.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>Up your content creation: </strong>Take a hands-free video with lush color and detail using Flex Mode. For even more clarity, Auto Frame Rate sets the optimal exposure so your video stays bright from start to finish.\r\\n<h2>Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5Performance</h2>\r\\n<h3>Operating System</h3>\r\\nSamsung Galaxy Z Fold 5 packed their priced foldable superphone with the latest Android 13, along with One UI 5.1.1. you will have a smoother user experience with the latest OS from Android, which comes with more customizable applications and features that let you have your way as you maximize your productivity and entertainment with the device.\r\\n<h3>Processing Power</h3>\r\\nAs a premium handset, the foldable Galaxy comes along with a powerful processing unit that plays a big role in providing extraordinary performance. The Qualcomm SM8550-AC Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 (4 nm) is intelligently engineered with groundbreaking AI across the board to enable truly extraordinary experiences. It delivers accelerated performance, unparalleled connectivity, champion-level gameplay, ingenious capture, and more. Enjoy super intuitive experiences like faster natural language processing with multi-language translation and transcription, AI cinematic video capture, direct voice command of your apps, AI bots for next-level gaming, and more.\r\\n\r\\nAlong with the Snapdragon chipset are Octa-core (1×3.36 GHz Cortex-X3 &amp; 2×2.8 GHz Cortex-A715 &amp; 2×2.8 GHz Cortex-A710 &amp; 3×2.0 GHz Cortex-A510) CPU and Adreno 740 GPU, both which are fundamental for seamless multi-tasking and uncompromised gaming experience.\r\\n<h3>Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5 Memory Space</h3>\r\\nThe Fold5 comes along with sufficient internal memory and RAM to run highly demanding tasks and store files and applications that require large storage capacity. Although the phone lacks a MicroSD slot for additional memory, it comes installed with:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>256GB 12GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>512GB 12GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>1TB 12GB RAM, all with UFS 4.0</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n12GB RAM is massive on any device, thus making the Galaxy Z Fold5 a superphone with great fast processing speed and the ability to carry out intensive tasks without difficulty.\r\\n<h3>Gaming</h3>\r\\nPower your road to victory with the upgraded hardware and software of the Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 Mobile Platform for Galaxy. This high-performance processor fuels champion-level gameplay.\r\\n<h3>Battery Performance</h3>\r\\nWith a long-lasting battery, you can give your phone all the attention it deserves. Paired with an advanced processor, Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5 efficiently adjusts power usage to your habits and your needs. Enjoy all day as you listen to music for 73 hours or 21 hours of watching your favorite movies before the need to recharge.\r\\n\r\\nYou can recharge the large, 4,400mAh non-removable battery using the 25W wired fast charging unit (recharges 1- 50% of the battery in 30 minutes. The powering system on the foldable Galaxy phone also supports 15W wireless charging and 4.5w reverse charging. As such, you can comfortably recharge your smart devices without any inconveniences.\r\\n<h3>Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 5 Maximize the Synchronized Galaxy Ecosystem</h3>\r\\nMulti Control lets you use a keyboard and mouse across devices including Galaxy Z Fold5 and Galaxy Tab S9, making it even easier to copy and paste or drag and drop. Galaxy-connected devices are perfect together, opening up new ways to seamlessly communicate, work, play and stay healthy.',NULL,NULL,'Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Fold-5','Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Fold-5',325000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(216,'Samsung Galaxy Z Fold4','Samsung Galaxy Z Fold4','Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Fold4','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,2,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Samsung Galaxy Z Fold4','<h2>Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 4 5G Specs in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<div class=\"product-details__text-area\">\r\\n\r\\nSamsung has been on a successful streak in manufacturing and delivering some of the best high-end handsets on the global market. The Samsung Galaxy Z Fold4 is designed and created to appeal to the eye and also unfold possibilities with new advanced technologies. The handset supports up to 5G network connectivity. It measures 155.1 x 67.1 x 14.2-15.8 mm when folded and 155.1 x 130.1 x 6.3 mm when unfolded. It weighs 263g. as such, it is a big and noticeable smartphone to carry around.\r\\n\r\\n</div>\r\\n<div>\r\\n\r\\nSamsung put everything into the foldable handset to make it stand out and function. Enjoy a large 7.6-inches of Foldable Dynamic AMOLED 2X display, whose refresh rate is at 120Hz, and emits 1200 nits at peak brightness. 1812 x 2176 pixels (~373 ppi density) is an assurance of optimal user experience, with Samsung living nothing uncompromised when it comes to maximum user experience. It certainly befits such a big smart device and the heavy price tag attached to it.\r\\n\r\\n</div>\r\\nRunning on Android 12L, One UI 4.1.1 OS, be assured of enjoying the latest Android software updates as well as Samsung’s applications which enhance your user experience.  An Octa-core, Qualcomm SM8475 Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 (4 nm) processor runs the handset in the background, keeping up with your commands and smooth functioning of the Samsung foldable device. 12GB RAM and 256GB / 512GB / 1TB internal memory is sufficient for the phablet on your palm. Demanding tasks will be no contest to the powerful processor coupled with the Adreno 730 GPU that ensures you immerse in your best video games without reservations on the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold4.\r\\n\r\\nTo enable the big handset to run its operations without inconveniences, a 4,400mAh non-removable battery is installed. This is quite limited power, considering the demands in the device’s output. However, do not worry too much as Samsung thought it all out and provided convenient ways to recharge the battery, through Fast charging 25W, Fast wireless charging 15W, and Reverse wireless charging 4.5W. Samsung Galaxy Z Fold4 is now available in Kenya and at Phoneplace Kenya for Kes 255,000. It comes in Grey-green, Phantom Black, Beige, and Burgundy where you can pick your favorite color choice.\r\\n<h3>Design and Build</h3>\r\\nThe Samsung Galaxy Z Fold4 is a piece of art in terms of design. It is complicated, sophisticated, and beautiful to behold. Measuring 155.1 x 67.1 x 14.2-15.8 mm when folded, It looks angular and thick with slightly curved edges and a distinctive, ergonomic design. Unfolding, its full splendor comes in display through the 7.6 inches display and 155.1 x 130.1 x 6.3 mm dimensions. Weighing up to 263g, Galaxy Z Fold4 is made of a Glass front (Gorilla Glass Victus+) (folded), plastic front (unfolded), glass back (Gorilla Glass Victus+), and aluminum frame. The foldable Samsung handset is as beautiful as it intimidating the first time you lay your hands on it.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nA dominant and excellent 7.6-inch, Foldable Dynamic AMOLED 2X, 120Hz, HDR10+, 1200 nits (peak) will hold you captive, as you immerse into the receptive, high resolution 1812 x 2176 pixels (~373 ppi density) screen.  The foldable screen may look delicate but a lot of engineering has gone into it to maximize performance and ensure a seamless, uncompromising user experience as far as using the display is concerned. 120Hz ensures peak performance of the display, by tasking the processor to keep things as refreshed as possible as you multi-task on the split screen or seek some entertainment. To protect the pricey display, Samsung invested in the Corning <a href=\"https://www.corning.com/gorillaglass/worldwide/en/glass-types/gorilla-glass-victus.html\">Gorilla Glass Victus+</a> making the screen scratch and dustproof.\r\\n<h3>Connectivity</h3>\r\\nSamsung Galaxy Z Fold 4 supports up to 5G Network Connectivity. It means faster data download, upload speeds, and connection when communicating on the network. A dual SIM (Nano) give you the option to choose your best network provider depending on their network coverage. The handset support e-SIM, meaning you can activate and benefit from a cellular plan by our carrier without having to see a physical nano-SIM. You can use dual SIMs, two active e-SIMs, or one Nano SIM and e-SIM depending on your preference\r\\n<h3>Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 4 Camera</h3>\r\\nIt has 2 fold front cameras. Samsung Galaxy Z Fold4 has a 4MP, f/1.8, 26mm (wide), 2.0µm, under-display selfie camera. The camera resolution is low, which could mean it is best not to place it there for selfies. It serves an important function of enabling video chats and enhancing security access to the device through the Face Recognition security feature.  The cover of the device features a single 10 MP, f/2.2, 24mm (wide), 1/3″, and 1.22µm. You would rather use the cover front camera for selfies than the 4MP in the unfolded device.\r\\n\r\\nThe main camera on the Galaxy Z Fold features a triple set-up having a primary 50 MP, f/1.8, 23mm (wide), 1.0µm, Dual Pixel PDAF, and OIS. The other lenses comprise 10 MP, f/2.4, 66mm (telephoto), 1.0µm, PDAF, OIS, 3x optical zoom and 12 MP, f/2.2, 123˚, 12mm (ultra-wide), 1.12µm. Samsung always delivers when it comes to cameras on their devices, and they did not disappoint on the Fold. The triple set-up camera at the rear of the handset features LED flash, HDR, and panorama. It can records awesome videos up to 4K@60fps, 1080p@60/240fps (gyro-EIS), 720p@960fps (gyro-EIS), HDR10+.\r\\n<h3>Performance</h3>\r\\nThe expectations on such a high-end handset are high, in regards to fast and efficient performance. The Fold does not disappoint. Running on the latest version of Android platforms-Android 12L, One UI 4.1.1- you will enjoy a seamless and unforgettable user experience with a user-friendly UI. To ensure efficiency and speed execution of commands on the display, the Fold is equipped with a powerful and proven Octa-core (1×3.19 GHz Cortex-X2 &amp; 3×2.75 GHz Cortex-A710 &amp; 4×1.80 GHz Cortex-A510). The processing power of the Octa-core is powerful enough to enable the smooth running of operations in the background, coupled with an equally efficient Qualcomm SM8475 Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 (4 nm) chipset. Whether you are multi-tasking on two separate screens or pushing hard for productivity, the processing power on the Fold will much and meet your demands and expectations. Adreno 730 GPU is equally efficient, enabling playing games on the device without the lags and stuttering.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nSuch a massive handset will demand a lot of power from its battery to keep up with the power needed to run operations. The Fold comes with a4, 400mAh non-removable battery installed. For an average user, the battery power can last for at least a day before the need for a recharge. To reduce inconvenience incidences causes by low or no power, Samsung invested in the latest technology to keep the Fold powered, on, and going strong. First, a Fast charging 25W wired adapter comes with the handset for fast charging. It powers up the battery from 0-50% in 30 minutes (as advertised). Secondly, Galaxy Z Fold supports fast wireless charging 15W. Thirdly, you can make use of reverse wireless charging 4.5W to power up your device and keep on working.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3142\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3142\" aria-describedby=\"tablepress-3142-description\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Samsung</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 4</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-4\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Announced</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>August 2022</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-5\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Released</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>August 2022</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-6\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>OS</div><