"column-2\">Unfolded: 155.1 x 130.1 x 6.3 mm\r\\nFolded: 155.1 x 67.1 x 14.2-15.8 mm</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-19\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Screen Resolution</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>1768 x 2208 pixels (~372 PPI density)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-20\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Type</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Main Display: Foldable Dynamic AMOLED 2X, 120Hz, HDR10+, 1200 nits (peak)\r\\nCover display: Dynamic AMOLED 2X, 120Hz, Corning Gorilla Glass Victus+</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-21\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Size</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Main Display: 7.6 inches, 181.8 cm2 (~89.9% screen-to-body ratio)</div>\r\\n<div>Cover display: 6.2 inches, 904 x 2316 pixels, 23.1:9 ratio</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-22\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>3.5mm jack</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>No\r\\n32-bit/384kHz audio\r\\nTuned by AKG</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-23\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Bluetooth</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>5.2, A2DP, LE, aptX HD</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-24\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPS</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>A-GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO, BDS</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-25\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>NFC</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Yes</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-26\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/6e, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-27\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>USB</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>USB Type-C 3.2</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-28\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Radio</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>No</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-29\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sensor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Fingerprint (side-mounted), accelerometer, gyro, proximity, compass, barometer\r\\nBixby natural language commands and dictation\r\\nSamsung DeX (desktop experience support)\r\\nSamsung Pay (Visa, MasterCard certified)\r\\nUltra Wideband (UWB) support</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-30\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Battery</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Li-Po 4400 mAh, non-removable</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-31\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Fast Charging</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Fast charging 25W\r\\nFast wireless charging 11W\r\\nReverse wireless charging 4.5W</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-32\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Colors</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Stalwart Phantom Black, Beige, and Gray-green</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Fold4','Samsung-Galaxy-Z-Fold4',225000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(217,'Samsung USB Type-C to Type-C','Samsung USB Type-C to Type-C','Samsung-USB-Type-C-to-Type-C','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,13,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Samsung USB Type-C to Type-C','<div class=\"electro-description clearfix\"><h2>Samsung USB Type-C to Type-C Cable</h2><div class=\"FeaturesTab__LogoDescriptionContainer-sc-16uhzud-0 dhIhSx\"><div>The Samsung USB Type-C to Type-C Cable price in Kenya is Ksh 1500. The Samsung USB-C Cable lets you charge your USB-C device as well as sync your photos',NULL,NULL,'Samsung-USB-Type-C-to-Type-C','Samsung-USB-Type-C-to-Type-C',1500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(218,'Tecno Camon 20','Tecno Camon 20','Tecno-Camon-20','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno Camon 20','<h2>Tecno Camon 20 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Physical Attributes</h3>\r\\nThe Tecno Camon 20 stands out with the geometric aesthetics on the back panel. The Camon Puzzle Deconstructionist Design incorporates geometric aesthetics and avant-garde fashion. Tyson Polygon creates visually striking and unconventional patterns. It breaks beyond the minimalist and mundane aesthetic sensibilities. Holding the phone makes you stand out. The phone’s body consists of an ultra-slim body measuring 7.8mm thick. The phone is also waterproof with ip53 ratings. Tecno Camon 20 is available in Predawn Black, Glacier Glow and Serenity Blue.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Camon Display</h3>\r\\nA large, high-resolution display dominates the Tecno phone. The screen measures 6.67 inches, with a rounded notch to accommodate the front-facing camera. The AMOLED show boasts a high 1080 x 2400 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~395 ppi density) resolution, making it great for digital experiences, watching videos and browsing the internet.\r\\n\r\\nThe immersive All-slim Bezel Design on the Tecno Camon 20 provides the following:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Always on Display Real Time Information Alerts</li>\r\\n 	<li>47% Bezel Narrowing</li>\r\\n 	<li>Dynamic Wallpaper gives an immersive experience.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe large screen has outstanding contrast and dynamic range. You can savour the stunning true-to-life colours and details of every photo on your screen. The eye protection dual shield consists of high-frequency dimming and 50% Blue-light harm reduction, hence comfortable to use even for long hours.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Camon 20 Processing Unit</h3>\r\\nTecno Camon 20 is created for power, precision and performance, even when considered a mid-tier phone. The phone has an efficient processing unit complemented with sufficient RAM and ROM. Anchored on the latest Android 13, HIOS 13, Camon 20 is powered by a decent MediaTek MT6769Z Helio G85 (12nm) chipset, supported by Octa-core (2×2.0 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.8 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU and Mali-G52 MC2 GPU. As a whole, the processing unit makes multitasking, gaming and intensive use of the phone manageable without lags and phone stuttering. For memory, a massive 256GB internal and 8GB RAM makes the Camon 20 stand out and highly preferred among mid-tier handsets in 2023. T\r\\n\r\\nhe large MEMORY CAPACITY AND UP TO 8GB RAM extended memory allow up to 18 Apps to run simultaneously and up to 6.5 million photos to be stored in the phone. You can hang on to your best memories and capture and keep them for as long as possible. Heating during intensive use, such as playing games, is standard among budget phones. For Tecno Camon 20, the large Graphene + High Polymer makes a triathlon of solid, liquid, ad gas thermal solutions to dissipate heat efficiently.  The highly technical and well-engineered cooling system is designed to instantly reduce heat to prevent lagging or stuttering during intense use.\r\\n<h3>Enhanced security.</h3>\r\\nConvenience and security are in sync with the Tecno Camon 20. The under-display fingerprint scanner enables convenient, high-speed unlocking. It is fast at 356 milliseconds. It unlocks the minute you touch the sensor. With a certified set of developed biometric anti-counterfeiting algorithms, security is locked in place when you open quickly.\r\\n<h3>Audio-Visual Output</h3>\r\\nTecno Camon 20 has Dual stereo Speakers with high bass synergy and DTS Professional Certification. This makes the audio and visual output when watching movies or listening to MP3s immersive and memorable. The dual stereo speakers are certified to offer CD-level sound quality. Playing games, you will enjoy the rich and full tonal quality of music and sound output.\r\\n<h3>Optimised Connectivity</h3>\r\\nThere is improved connectivity and experience even under a weak network. Camon 20 has prioritised front-end smoothness via network allocation and multi-network synergy. Network performance in loading TikTok videos is up by q0%, and Communication fluency is up by 25%. As such, you can enjoy an uninterrupted network experience even in areas with poor network coverage or weak peak hours.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Camon 20 Battery</h3>\r\\nTecno Camon 20 is powered by a 5,000mAh battery. A fast, wired 33W charger recharges lithium battery. The battery will give you reliable service on day-to-night usage. You won’t necessarily need to spend your money on a power bank to supplement the power needs of the handset. The extended duration mode is about 1 hour longer than on previous models. The smart power-saving method is about 10 hours longer. You can extend the battery life using the AI Smart Charge.',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-Camon-20','Tecno-Camon-20',30500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(219,'Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G','Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G','Tecno-Camon-20-Pro-4G','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G','<h2>Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Physical Attributes</h3>\r\\nThe Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G stands out with the geometric aesthetics on the back panel. The Camon Puzzle Deconstructionist Design incorporates geometric aesthetics and avant-garde fashion. Tyson Polygon creates visually striking and unconventional patterns. It breaks beyond the minimalist and mundane aesthetic sensibilities. Holding the phone makes you stand out. The phone’s body consists of an ultra-slim body measuring 8.2 mm thick. The phone is also waterproof with IP53 ratings. Camon 20 is available in Predawn Black and Serenity Blue.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G Display</h3>\r\\nA large, high-resolution display dominates the Tecno phone. The screen measures 6.67 inches, with a rounded notch to accommodate the front-facing camera. The AMOLED show boasts a high 1080 x 2400 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~395 ppi density) resolution, making it great for digital experiences, watching videos and browsing the internet. The immersive All-slim Bezel Design on the Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G provides the following:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Always on Display Real Time Information Alerts</li>\r\\n 	<li>47% Bezel Narrowing</li>\r\\n 	<li>Dynamic Wallpaper gives an immersive experience.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe large screen has outstanding contrast and dynamic range. You can savour the stunning true-to-life colours and details of every photo on your screen. The eye protection dual shield consists of high-frequency dimming and 50% Blue-light harm reduction, hence comfortable to use even for long hours.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G Processing Unit</h3>\r\\nTecno Camon 20 Pro 4G is created for power, precision and performance, even when considered a mid-tier phone. The phone has an efficient processing unit complemented with sufficient RAM and ROM. Anchored on the latest Android 13, HIOS 13, Camon 20 Pro is powered by a decent MediaTek MT8781 Helio G99 (6nm) chipset, supported by Octa-core (2×2.2 GHz Cortex-A76 &amp; 6×2.0 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU and Mali-G57 MC2GPU. As a whole, the processing unit makes multitasking, gaming and intensive use of the phone manageable without lags and phone stuttering.\r\\n\r\\nFor memory, a massive 256GB internal and 8GB RAM makes the Tecno Camon 20 Pro 4G stand out and highly preferred among mid-tier handsets in 2023. The large memory capacity and up to 8GB RAM extended memory allow up to 18 Apps to run simultaneously and up to 6.5 million photos to be stored in the phone. You can hang on to your best memories and capture and keep them for as long as possible. Heating during intensive use, such as playing games, is standard among budget phones. For Tecno Camon 20 Pro, the large Graphene + High Polymer makes a triathlon of solid, liquid, ad gas thermal solutions to dissipate heat efficiently.  The highly technical and well-engineered cooling system is designed to instantly reduce heat to prevent lagging or stuttering during intense use.\r\\n<h3>Camera set-up</h3>\r\\nCapture awesome selfies with the 32MP lens. Make memory worth it with good shots using the triple camera at the back of the phone. The camera consists of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>64 MP, f/1.7, 25mm (wide), 1/1.7″, 0.8µm, PDAF</li>\r\\n 	<li>2 MP, f/2.4, (depth)</li>\r\\n 	<li>QVGA</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nYou will be able to record 1080p@30fps videos, which is above average in terms of output and delivery.\r\\n<h3>Enhanced security.</h3>\r\\nConvenience and security are in sync with the Tecno Camon 20 Pro. The under-display fingerprint scanner enables convenient, high-speed unlocking. It is fast at 356 milliseconds. It unlocks the minute you touch the sensor. With a certified set of developed biometric anti-counterfeiting algorithms, security is locked in place when you open quickly.\r\\n<h3>Audio-Visual Output</h3>\r\\nTecno Camon 20 Pro 4G has stereo Speakers with high bass synergy and DTS Professional Certification. This makes the audio and visual output when watching movies or listening to MP3s immersive and memorable. The dual stereo speakers are certified to offer CD-level sound quality. Playing games, you will enjoy the rich and full tonal quality of music and sound output.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nTecno Camon 20 Pro is powered by a 5,000mAh battery. A fast, wired 33W charger recharges lithium battery. The battery will give you reliable service on day-to-night usage. You won’t necessarily need to spend your money on a power bank to supplement the power needs of the handset. The extended duration mode is about 1 hour longer than on previous models. The smart power-saving method is about 10 hours longer. You can extend the battery life using the AI Smart Charge.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3381\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3381\" aria-labelledby=\"tablepress-3381-name\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Tecno</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Camon 20 Pro 4G</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-4\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Announced</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>May, 2023</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-5\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Released</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>May, 2023</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-6\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Operating System</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Android 13, HIOS 13</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-7\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Chipset</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Mediatek MT8781 Helio G99 (6nm)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-8\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>CPU Speed</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Octa-core (2×2.2 GHz Cortex-A76 &amp; 6×2.0 GHz Cortex-A55)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-9\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPU</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Mali-G57 MC2</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-10\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Storage</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>128GB/256GB</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-11\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>RAM</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>8GB</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-12\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Card Slot</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Unspecified</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-13\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Rear Camera</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">64 MP + 2 MP + QVGA</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-14\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Front Camera</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>32 MP</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-15\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Network</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>GSM / HSPA / LTE</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-16\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sim Card</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Dual SIM (Nano-SIM, dual stand-by)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-17\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Screen Resolution</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">1080 x 2400 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~395 ppi density)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-18\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Dimensions</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">162.7 x 75.9 x 7.8 mm (6.41 x 2.99 x 0.31 in)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-19\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Type</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">AMOLED, 120Hz</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-20\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Size</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">6.67 inches, 107.4 cm2 (~87.0% screen-to-body ratio)</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-21\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Bluetooth</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">5.2, A2DP, LE</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-22\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPS</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Dual-band A-GPS, GLONASS</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-23\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>NFC</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Yes</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-24\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n, dual-band</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-25\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>USB</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>USB Type-C 2.0, OTG</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-26\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Radio</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>FM radio</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-27\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sensor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Fingerprint (under display, optical), accelerometer, proximity, compass</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-28\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Battery</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Li-Po 5000 mAh, non-removable</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-29\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Fast Charging</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">33W wired</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</tab