\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>16 MP</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-15\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Network</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>GSM / HSPA / LTE / 5G</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-16\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sim Card</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Dual SIM (Nano-SIM, dual stand-by)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-17\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Weight</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>299 g (10.55 oz)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-18\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Dimensions</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Unfolded: 159.4 x 140.4 x 6.9 mm\r\\nFolded: 159.4 x 72 x 14.2-14.5 mm</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-19\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Screen Resolution</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>2000 x 2296 pixels (~388 ppi density)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-20\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Type</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Foldable LTPO AMOLED, 1B colors, 120Hz, 1100 nits (peak)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-21\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Size</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>7.85 inches, 196.9 cm2 (~88.0% screen-to-body ratio)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-22\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>3.5mm jack</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>No</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-23\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Bluetooth</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>5.2, A2DP, LE</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-24\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPS</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO, BDS</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-25\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>NFC</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Yes</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-26\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-27\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>USB</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>USB Type-C, OTG</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-28\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Radio</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>FM radio</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-29\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sensor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Fingerprint (side-mounted), accelerometer, gyro, proximity, compass</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-30\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Battery</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Li-Po 5000 mAh, non-removable</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-31\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Fast Charging</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>45W wired, 40% in 15 min, 100% in 55 min</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-32\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Colors</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Black, White</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-Phantom-V-FOLD','Tecno-Phantom-V-FOLD',135000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(222,'Tecno Phantom X2','Tecno Phantom X2','Tecno-Phantom-X2','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno Phantom X2','<h2>Tecno Phantom X2 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Design and Build</h3>\r\\nPhantom X2 is a premium device by Tecno that boasts a great design and build. It weighs 203g and measures 164.6 x 72.7 x 8.9 mm. Released to the Kenyan market in early 2023, the X2 comes in 2 unique colors: Stardust Gray and Moonlight Silver. A large bright display dominates the front while the back has a protruding camera deck that protects the main camera set-up. In terms of build, the X2 comes with a Glass front, polycarbonate back, and aluminum frame body material.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nTecno Phantom X2 features a 6.8-inch AMOLED display with a 1080 x 2400 pixels resolution. A high 120Hz refresh is sufficient to keep in peak performance when in use protecting the AMOLED display is a Corning Gorilla Glass Victus that is tamper-proof. The display provides a superior viewing experience for content consumption and excellent browsing experiences.\r\\n<h3>Processing Power</h3>\r\\nRunning in the background and enabling smooth operations of the applications on the handset is an Android 12, complemented with HIOS 12 skin cover. As a user, you are assured of fast processing speeds and no lags when multitasking and playing games thanks to an Octa-core processor, coupled with Mali-G710 MC10 GPU.\r\\n\r\\nAny smartphone’s processing power and optimal functioning largely depend on the internal storage space available. The X2 comes with an inbuilt storage of  256GB 8GB RAM. The storage is quite sufficient, considering Tecno so no need for additional external memory.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Phantom X2 Cameras</h3>\r\\nTecno invests heavily in its camera to give users exceptional and memorable experiences when it comes o optics. Tecno Phantom X2 comes installed with a triple main camera set up consisting of 64 MP, f/1.7, (wide) camera + 13 MP, f/2.2, (ultrawide) lens+ 2 MP sensor. The set not only captures high-quality snaps but also 4K@30/60fps, and 1080p@30fps videos.\r\\n\r\\nAt the front, the X2 is packed with a 32 MP, f/2.5, (wide) single camera that will enable you to capture great life moments with family and friends. The selfie camera is capable of taking 1080p video shots. And LED flash enables capturing images and videos in low light.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Phantom X2 Network</h3>\r\\nPhantom X2 is a 5G-enabled device. Enjoy fast uploading and downloading speeds of videos, pictures, and multimedia.\r\\n<h3>Communications</h3>\r\\nThe 5G-enabled device supports Bluetooth pairing and WLAN connectivity. GPS installed on it enabled tracking and accurate identification of locations, especially for motorists. The X2 supports FM Radio, and has a loudspeaker but interestingly has no 3.5mm jack port. For fast data transfer, USB Type-C 2.0, OTG will be useful for the handset handler. For convenience when communicating using the Phantom, make use of the display, and optical fingerprint scanner. other sensors installed on the device are the accelerometer, gyro, compass, and proximity sensors.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nPowering the Phantom X2 is a 5,160mAh battery. For charging, the handset supports fast charging with a 45W wired adapter that is capable of charging 1-54% of the battery in 20 min, and 100% within 1 hour.\r\\n<h2>Pros and Cons of the Tecno Phantom X2</h2>\r\\n<h3>Pros</h3>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Powerful battery at 5160mAh</li>\r\\n 	<li>The fast and efficient processor</li>\r\\n 	<li>Above average camera</li>\r\\n 	<li>Supports fast charger</li>\r\\n 	<li>Massive internal storage</li>\r\\n 	<li>5G network enabled.</li>\r\\n 	<li>4K Video recording capability.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Cons</h3>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>No slot for an additional memory slot</li>\r\\n 	<li>No optical zooming</li>\r\\n 	<li>No reverse and wireless charging options</li>\r\\n 	<li>Above-average camera performance</li>\r\\n 	<li>Not water resistant</li>\r\\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-Phantom-X2','Tecno-Phantom-X2',72000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(223,'Tecno Phantom X2 Pro','Tecno Phantom X2 Pro','Tecno-Phantom-X2-Pro','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno Phantom X2 Pro','<h2>Tecno Phantom X2 Pro Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Design and Build</h3>\r\\nThe Tecno Phantom X2 Pro has an ergonomic design that resembles the Phantom X2. Measuring 164.6 x 72.7 x 9 mm and weighing 201g, the device has nicely rounded edges, a flat front, and back, with a slight camera bump. The Unibody Double-Curved Design is a confirmation of the master touch on the X2 Pro. It has a precision-crafted streamline and delicate texture.\r\\n\r\\nIt is a piece of art that lances futuristic aesthetics and extreme hand feeling. With the X2 Pro, you will feel the ultimate elegance at a touch. The device is made from a plastic back, glass front (Gorilla Glass Victus), and aluminum frame.\r\\n<h3>Camera Set-up</h3>\r\\nThe selfie camera comprises of a powerful, single 32MP (wide)  camera capable of taking high-quality snaps and 1080p@30fps video shots.  At the rear end, the Phantom X2 Pro packs a triple camera set-up consisting of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>50 MP, f/1.9, (wide), 1/1.3″, 1.2µm, PDAF camera</li>\r\\n 	<li>50 MP, f/1.5, 65mm (telephoto), PDAF, 2.5x optical zoom, retractable lens</li>\r\\n 	<li>13 MP, f/2.2, (ultrawide) sensor.</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nLike the Phantom X2 main camera, the X2 Pro is capable of taking 4K@30/60fps, and 1080p@30fps video shots and recordings. The LED flash provides the option of taking excellent shots in dim light, while panorama and HDR enable the use of alternatives when it comes to choosing from a variety of options that suits the occasion and moment.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nTecno invested in a tamper-proof, Corning Gorilla Glass Victus protector. Boasting a 6.8-inch AMOLED display, the Phantom X2 Pro screen is modest and will give the user a great experience when browsing the internet or browsing through multimedia. A high 120Hz refresh rate keeps the device at peak, with no slags during use. 500 nits provide the use with above-average brightness which enhances user experiences. combining the 500 nits of brightness with ~387 PPI density makes the Phantom X2 Pro one of the best high-end smartphones available on the market in 2023.\r\\n<h3>Performance.</h3>\r\\nTecno Phantom X2 Pro runs on Android 12, complemented with <a href=\"https://www.tecno-mobile.com/hios/\">HIOS 12</a> software skin. A more customizable UI enables better user experiences and use in most preferred appearances. An Octa-core, MediaTek Dimensity 9000 (4 nm) processor and Mali-G710 MC10 GPU are essential in enabling speedier response to user commands, multi-tasking, and playing video games on the handset. A MediaTek Dimensity 9000 (4 nm) chipset is considerably faster, more efficient, and more powerful compared to previous chipsets installed on techno devices.\r\\n\r\\nEnabling smooth running of applications on the Phantom X2 Pro is 256GB 12GB RAM internally built memory space. The space is quite sufficient, and it is reasonable that Tecno did not consider having a card slot on the device.\r\\n<h3>Network</h3>\r\\nTecno has taken up an aggressive stance in developing high-end smartphones, with the Phantom X2 Pro, like its X2 predecessor being 5G enabled. With the handset, the user is certain of fast uploading and downloading speeds, besides great experiences when browsing the internet and accessing heavy files online.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nPowering the Tecno device is a powerful 5,160mAh battery that enables lighting up the large and bright screen on Phantom X2 Pro, applications in the background, and responding to multiple commands on the display. Supporting the massive battery is a 45W wired charger, capable of charging 1-54% of the battery in 20 minutes and 100% in 60 minutes.\r\\n<h3>Pros and Cons of Phantom X2 Pro</h3>\r\\n<h3>Pros</h3>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Powerful battery</li>\r\\n 	<li>Fast charging support</li>\r\\n 	<li>Powerful and efficient chipset (MediaTek Dimensity 9000 (4 nm))</li>\r\\n 	<li>Fingerprint sensor support</li>\r\\n 	<li>120Hz refresh rate</li>\r\\n 	<li>High resolution on display at 1080 x 2400 pixels</li>\r\\n 	<li>Corning Gorilla Glass Victus protection</li>\r\\n 	<li>Has the world’s first retractable portrait lens</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Cons</h3>\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Average cameras set-up</li>\r\\n 	<li>No wireless and reverse charging</li>\r\\n 	<li>High internal memory</li>\r\\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-Phantom-X2-Pro','Tecno-Phantom-X2-Pro',89999,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(224,'Tecno POP 7','Tecno POP 7','Tecno-POP-7','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno POP 7','<h2>Tecno Pop 7 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\nThe Tecno Pop 7 price in Kenya is 13,500 shillings. The Tecno Pop 7 has a 6.6-inch display with an HD+ resolution of 720 x 1612 pixels. It features a Mediatek Helio A22 quad-core processor coupled with 2 GB of RAM and 64 GB of storage. For more storage, it has a microSD card slot. The Pop 7 packs a 5,000mAh battery that supports 10W charging and runs on Android 12 Go edition, which is overlaid with HiOS 8.6. The display notch houses a 5-megapixel selfie camera. There is an LED flash on the top bezel of the device for snapping brighter selfies in dim-light conditions. Its back panel has an 8-megapixel main camera, a depth sensor, and an LED flash. The Tecno Pop 7 comes in Endless Black, and Capri Blue colors\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3196\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3196\" aria-describedby=\"tablepress-3196-description\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Tecno</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Tecno Pop7</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-4\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Announced</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">2023, March 28</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-5\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Released</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">2023, March 28</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-6\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Operating System</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Android 12 (Go edition), HiOS 8.6</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-7\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Chipset</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Mediatek MT6761 Helio A22 (12 nm)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-8\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>CPU Speed</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2