lass=\"row-21\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Display Size</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>6.6 inches, 104.6 cm2 (~83.2% screen-to-body ratio)</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-22\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>3.5mm jack</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Yes</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-23\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Bluetooth</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Yes</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-24\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>GPS</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>A-GPS</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-25\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>NFC</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>No</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-26\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Wi-Fi</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Yes</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-27\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>USB</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>microUSB 2.0, USB On-The-Go</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-28\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Radio</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>FM radio</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-29\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Sensor</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Fingerprint (side-mounted), accelerometer, proximity</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-30\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Battery</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Li-Po 5000 mAh, non-removable</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-31\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Colors</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">Endless Black, Capri Blue</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-POP-7','Tecno-POP-7',14500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(225,'Tecno POP 7 Pro','Tecno POP 7 Pro','Tecno-POP-7-Pro','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno POP 7 Pro','<h2>Tecno POP 7 Pro Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\nThe Tecno Pop 7 Pro price in Kenya is from Ksh 14,500. It features a 6.56-inch IPS LCD (display) with an HD+ resolution of 720 x 1612 pixels. The handset is powered by a Quad-core, Mediatek Helio A22 processor, cushioned by 3GB of RAM and 64GB internal storage (ROM). For more storage, it has a microSD card slot. The Tecno Pop 7 Pro packs a 5,000mAh battery that supports 10W charging and runs on Android 12 Go edition, which is overlaid with HiOS 12 skin. The display notch houses a 5-megapixel selfie camera. There is an LED flash on the top bezel of the device for snapping brighter selfies in dim-light conditions. Its back panel has a 13MP (wide) main camera + QVGA, and Dual-LED flash.\r\\n<h3>General build</h3>\r\\nThe device measures 163.9 x 75.5 x 8.9 mm and weighs 183g. the body and body frame are made of plastic, while the front is made of glass. Too bad the handset is not waterproof and does not have a display protector. At least it has a rear-mounted fingerprint scanner.\r\\n<h3>Display</h3>\r\\nThe Tecno handset features a 6.56-inch waterdrop notch display with 720 x 1612 pixels resolution. The IPS LCD Display has 480 nits peak brightness, which is average but decent enough for required functionalities.\r\\n<h3>Tecno POP 7 Pro Camera specifications</h3>\r\\nThe selfie camera consists of a single 5MP Camera with LED Flash. With 5MP, you will get the job done, but Tecno could do better. The primary camera consists of a dual set-up of a 13 MP, (wide), AF+ QVGA. A dual LED Flash and HDR give you options when taking photo shots. Besides, the main camera is capable of taking 1080p videos, which could be handy as you party, work in the office or are out on a long safari and need to capture moments for memory’s sake.\r\\n<h3>Platform and Processing capacity</h3>\r\\nTecno Pop 7 Pro runs on Android 12, HiOS 12 OS. You are assured of decent performance, with the Pop 7 Pro, which is powered by a MediaTek MT6761 Helio A22 (12 nm) chipset, Quad-core 2.0 GHz Cortex-A53 CPU, and PowerVR GE8320 GPU. Enjoy upgraded applications and Tecno’s friendly UI when you switch on and start using the device. You will undoubtedly enjoy multi-tasking, playing low-setting games, and consuming multi-media on your device. 64GB 3GB RAM inbuilt memory space is sufficient, besides the MicroSDXC which gives you a breather as you seek more space for your applications and media content.\r\\n<h3>Tecno POP 7 Pro Communication, Sensors, and Connectivity</h3>\r\\nTecno Pop 7 Pro is a 4 G-enabled smartphone. It supports up to 4G Bands and utilizes HSPA, LTE network speeds. The handset supports Bluetooth pairing, GPS, OTG (MicroUSB 2.0, USB On-The-Go), FM Radio with a 3.5mm Jack, and WLAN (Wi-Fi, Hotspot). Several sensors are installed on the device. They include Fingerprint (rear-mounted), accelerometer, and proximity.\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nThe device has a massive and decent 5,000mAh non-removable battery. Besides, it does have a 10W fast charger which makes it convenient to recharge the device fast on the go and avoid low power disappointments.\r\\n\r\\n&nbsp;\r\\n<table>\r\\n<tbody>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>BRAND</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Tecno</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>MODEL</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Pop 7 Pro</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>TYPE</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Hand-held, portable smartphone</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\"></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>LAUNCH DATE</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">January 28<sup>th</sup>, 2023</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>AVAILABILITY</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Yes. Now available on the market</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>PHYSICAL ATTRIBUTES</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Weight: 183g,\r\\n\r\\nDimensions: 163.9 x 75.5 x 8.9 mm,\r\\n\r\\nBuild: Glass front, plastic back, plastic frame\r\\n\r\\nSIM Card: Dual</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>DISPLAY</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Size: 6.56 inches,\r\\n\r\\nType: IPS LCD\r\\n\r\\nScreen protector: None</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>WATERPROOF</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">No</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>CAMERAS</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Selfie Camera: 5MP\r\\n\r\\nMain Camera: 13MP + QVGA.</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>PROCESSING UNIT</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">CPU: Quad-core 2.0 GHz Cortex-A53,\r\\n\r\\nGPU: PowerVR GE8320\r\\n\r\\nChipset: MediaTek MT6761 Helio A22 (12 nm</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>OS</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Android 12, HIOS 12</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>SENSORS</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Rear-mounted fingerprint scanner, Accelerometer, Proximity Sensor</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>COMMUNICATION AND NETWORK</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">Network support: Up to 4G, Radio: supported, NFC: Not supported, Loudspeaker: Supported, 3.5mm jack: installed, GPS: Supported</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr>\r\\n<td width=\"168\"><strong>BATTERY</strong></td>\r\\n<td width=\"456\">5000mAh non-removable battery, 10W wired fast charging adapter.</td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n</tbody>\r\\n</table>',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-POP-7-Pro','Tecno-POP-7-Pro',14500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(226,'Tecno POP 7 Pro - 3GB','Tecno POP 7 Pro - 3GB','Tecno-POP-7-Pro-3GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno POP 7 Pro - 3GB','Tecno POP 7 Pro - 3GB',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-POP-7-Pro-3GB','Tecno-POP-7-Pro-3GB',15500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(227,'Tecno POP 7 Pro - 4GB','Tecno POP 7 Pro - 4GB','Tecno-POP-7-Pro-4GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno POP 7 Pro - 4GB','Tecno POP 7 Pro - 4GB',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-POP-7-Pro-4GB','Tecno-POP-7-Pro-4GB',16500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(228,'Tecno Pop 8','Tecno Pop 8','Tecno-Pop-8','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno Pop 8','<h2><strong>Tecno Pop 8 Specifications in Kenya</strong></h2>\r\\nThe Tecno Pop 8 price in Kenya is ksh 14,000 shillings. It has a 6.6-inch display with an IPS LCD HD+ resolution of 720 x 1612 pixels. The Tecno Pop 8 features an Octa-core Unisoc T606 (12 nm) processor with 64GB 3GB RAM / 64GB 4GB RAM / 128GB 4GB RAM of storage. For more storage, it has a microSD card slot. The Pop 8 packs a 5,000mAh battery that supports 10W charging and runs on Android 13 (Go edition). The display notch houses an 8-megapixel selfie camera. There is an LED flash on the device’s top bezel for snapping brighter selfies in dim-light conditions. Its back panel has a 13MP + 0.08MP primary camera with dual-LED flash. The Tecno Pop 8 comes in Mystery White, Alpenglow Gold, Magic Skin, and Gravity Black.\r\\n<h4>General Body Build</h4>\r\\nThe handset measures 163.7 x 75.6 x 8.6 mm. The Square Shape 2.0 of Pop 7 is a breakthrough in the phone’s unibody design.  The 8.6 mm thickness is impressive on a budget phone, slimmer than 8.9mm on Pop 7. Prep for a posh texture and design overhaul! The slim body comes in two styles: Rainbow Ring for a pop of color burst And Magic Skin 2.0 for a luxury sensation that feels like premium leather – crafted from 100% Hazard-free high-polymer silicone! Tecno Pop 8 comes in Trendy Colours. The fashionable bright colors of the Pop 7 series have captured the latest color trends. The colors available on the Pop 7 model are:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Mystery White</li>\r\\n 	<li>Alpenglow Gold,</li>\r\\n 	<li>Magic Skin</li>\r\\n 	<li>Gravity Black</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nThe body and frame are made of plastic, while the front is made of glass. The handset needs to be waterproof and have a display protector. At least it has a side-mounted fingerprint scanner.\r\\n<h4>Display</h4>\r\\nEnjoy chatting, playing games, and watching movies on the large and bright 6.6-inch IPS LCD on the Tecno Pop 8. With the big screen, enjoy a visual world of delight. The screen provides an average visual experience, and AI brightness dimming and eye protection mode also help minimize eye fatigue. 720 x 1612 pixels resolution and 480 nits peak brightness are enough for the required functionalities.\r\\n<h5>Self-developed Dynamic Port</h5>\r\\nWelcome aboard TECNO’s ingenious Dynamic Port, seamlessly integrated into the screen display. Intuitive UI brings efficient notifications – Stay in the know without frequent unlocking, checking, or app switching. Traditional mode is also available for your flexibility.\r\\n<h4>Camera Specifications</h4>\r\\n<h5>Main Camera.</h5>\r\\nThe primary camera comprises a dual camera set-up made up of the following:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>13 MP, f/1.8, (wide), 1.12µm, AF primary camera</li>\r\\n 	<li>08 MP (auxiliary lens) supporting lens</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h5>Dual Flash Selfie Camera</h5>\r\\nDusk to dawn, in or out, the selfie master on the front is always here to deliver! 8MP camera for sharp clarity, with light-sensitive pixel, dual flash, and screen fill light for your radiant glow. Plus, battle-tested beauty enhancements for every skin tone! Step into the spotlight and let your inner star shine doubly.\r\\n<h5>13MP HDR Portrait Camera</h5>\r\\nSuper-Wide aperture + Super-Large pixel unit. Let the SUPER DUO on the back supercharge your portraits in all lighting. Undimmed even in the backlight! HDR merges frames for clarity to outshine, while background blur crafts a stage for you to star. Capture beauty whenever, wherever.\r\\n<h6><em>AR Shot</em></h6>\r\\nExpress your vibrant self with playful cartoon avatars, lively backgrounds, and various AR elements.\r\\nStand out and steal the show!\r\\n<h4>Platform And Processing Capacity</h4>\r\\nTecno Pop 8 runs on Android 13 (Go edition). You are assured of above-average performance with the Pop 8, powered by a <a href=\"https://nanoreview.net/en/soc/unisoc-t606\">Unisoc T606</a> (12 nm) chipset, Octa-core (2×1.6 GHz Cortex-A75 &amp; 6×1.6 GHz Cortex-A55) CPU, and Mali-G57 MP1. Enjoy upgraded applications and Tecno’s friendly UI when you switch on and use the device. You will undoubtedly enjoy multi-tasking, playing low-setting games, and consuming multimedia on your device.\r\\n\r\\n64GB 3GB RAM, 64GB 4GB RAM, and 128GB 4GB RAM inbuilt memory space are sufficient, besides the MicroSDXC, which gives you options for additional memory for your applications and media content. Download music and videos, and save photos without worrying about storage. 1GB RAM expansion by default and up to 2GB RAM Extended RAM 2.0 allows up to 2GB of storage memory to be used as RAM to keep the phone running smoothly and fast.\r\\n<h4>Communication, Sensors, and Connectivity</h4>\r\\nTecno Pop 8 is a 4 G-enabled smartphone.\r\\n\r\\nIt supports 4G Bands and utilizes HSPA, LTE network speeds.\r\\n\r\\nThe handset supports Bluetooth pairing, GPS, OTG (MicroUSB 2.0, USB On-The-Go), FM Radio with a 3.5mm Jack, and WLAN (Wi-Fi, Hotspot).\r\\n\r\\nSeveral sensors are installed on the device. They include Fingerprint (rear-mounted), accelerometer, and proximity.\r\\n<h4>Battery</h4>\r\\nPowering the handset is a massive 5000mAh non-removable lithium battery. Enjoy a visual world of delight with long-lasting battery life so you can use your phone without worrying about low battery. It has a 10W fast charger, making it convenient to recharge the device quickly and avoid low-power disappointments.\r\\n\r\\nThree battery modes come along with the phone to help you manage the power, depending on your situation and preferences. The modes are:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Long battery life</li>\r\\n 	<li>Super power saving</li>\r\\n 	<li>Smart power saving mode.</li>\r\\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-Pop-8','Tecno-Pop-8',14500,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(229,'Tecno Pop 8 - 128GB','Tecno Pop 8 - 128GB','Tecno-Pop-8-128GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno Pop 8 - 128GB','Tecno Pop 8 - 128GB',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-Pop-8-128GB','Tecno-Pop-8-128GB',19000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(230,'Tecno Pop 8 - 64GB','Tecno Pop 8 - 64GB','Tecno-Pop-8-64GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno Pop 8 - 64GB','Tecno Pop 8 - 64GB',NULL,NULL,'Tecno-Pop-8-64GB','Tecno-Pop-8-64GB',15000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(231,'Tecno Spark 10','Tecno Spark 10','Tecno-Spark-10','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,3,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Tecno Spark 10','<h2>Tecno Spark 10 Specifications in Kenya</h2>\r\\n<h3>Build and Display</h3>\r\\nMeasuring 163.9 x 75.4 x 8.4 mm and weighing 202g, Tecno Spark 10 is an ergonomically designed handset that fits modern-day users’ rigours and demands. It is made of Glass front, plastic frame, and plastic back. The phone is a twin SIM available in Black, Blue, and White colors. It features a 6.6-inch IPS LCD with a 90Hz refresh rate and 720 x 1612 pixels, 20:9 ratio (~267 ppi density) resolution.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Spark 10 Main Camera</h3>\r\\nThe primary camera features a dual set-up consisting of 50MP + 0.08MP lenses. The 50MP high-resolution photography system helps capture the glamour of life whenever, wherever, and however, you want with crisp, high-quality photos.\r\\n<h3>Selfies</h3>\r\\nMake use of the 8MP to capture selfies and video chats. It could have had better pixelation for best shots and videos, hence a chance you can get disappointed. You can only make average shots at the back using the dual set-up of 8 MP, f/2.0, (wide) + 0.08 MP (depth) cameras.\r\\n<h4>3 Levels of Adjustable Brightness</h4>\r\\nLack of light should not limit your chance to take the perfect selfie. Spark 10 sparks it with a built-in front flashlight with three adjustable brightness levels to suit different lighting needs. Bright or dark, it invariably captures your highlight moments. 10lux soft light illuminates beauty without glaring in the eyes.\r\\n<h3>Tecno Spark 10 Performance</h3>\r\\nSpark 10 runs on Android 13, customizable using HIOS 12, Running in the background to ensure smooth operations whether browsing the internet, opening multiple applications, playing videos, or streaming videos is an Octa-core (4×2.3 GHz Cortex-A53 &amp; 4×1.7 GHz Cortex-A53) CPU and PowerVR GE8320 GPU.\r\\n\r\\nA massive 128GB internal memory and 8GB RAM support the handset’s operations and enable the optimal running of applications. Additional memory is supported, thanks to the dedicated MicroSD slot.\r\\n<h3>Network and Communications</h3>\r\\nIt is a 4G smartphone, supporting up to 4G network connectivity. It features a fingerprint scanner (side-mounted) that helps to enhance security access to the phone. Other sensors include an accelerometer, compass, and proximity sensor. A 3.5mm jack port and FM radio make it an ideal phone when addicted to listening to your favorite FM shows and hits. Besides, you can listen, watch and call on hands-free using headsets.\r\\n\r\\nTo get the best internet, use the Wi-Fi connectivity provision (802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band) on the Spark 10. It also comes with Bluetooth for pairing devices and sharing files. For accurate tracking and location, make use of GPS.\r\\n<h3>Phone Powering System</h3>\r\\nStay in power for long as you work, chat, or play your favorite game. Back in power fast with the 18W fast charger. The 5,000mAh is powerful enough to sustain long hours of gaming or phone calls. When running out of power, plug in the 18W rapid charger, and return to the business in no time.\r\\n<table id=\"tablepress-3107\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-3107\" aria-describedby=\"tablepress-3107-description\">\r\\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\r\\n<tr class=\"row-2\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Brand</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"column-2\">\r\\n<div>Tecno</div></td>\r\\n</tr>\r\\n<tr class=\"row-3\">\r\\n<td class=\"column-1\">\r\\n<div>Model</div></td>\r\\n<td class=\"c