heavier than the Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 5G. Redmi 13 Pro is dual SIM (Nano-SIM, dual standby), allowing you to choose the best networks to subscribe to and enjoy the services.  The device is IP54 rated, being both water and dustproof. Redmi Note 13 Pro comes in Black, White and Blue, hence a wide array of colours depending on your taste and preferences.\r\\n<h3>Redmi Note 13 Pro Display Specifications</h3>\r\\nThe handset boasts a bright, 6.67-inch Samsung AMOLED display with a 120Hz refresh rate, which is way better than IPS LCD and TFT screens on some handsets. At 1,800 nits peak brightness and 1220 x 2712 pixels resolution, you are assured of great gaming experiences, exploring the internet and browsing through multimedia. The exemplary display is worth protecting; hence, kudos to the Redmi team for the tamper-proof Corning Gorilla Glass Victus installed on the handset.\r\\n<h3>Redmi Note 13 Pro Cameras</h3>\r\\nInstalled on the handset is a 16 MP, single, selfie camera capable of taking decent image shots and 1080p@30 video recording.\r\\n\r\\nPacked at the handset’s rear is a robust, triple camera set-up consisting of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>200 MP, f/1.7, (wide), 1/1.4″, 0.56µm, multi-directional PDAF, OIS</li>\r\\n 	<li>8 MP, f/2.2, 120˚ (ultrawide), 1/4″, 1.12µm</li>\r\\n 	<li>2 MP, f/2.4, (macro) lens</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nEquipped with a 200MP ultra-clear main camera, the Xiaomi Imaging Brain AI algorithm is powerfully supported, and software and hardware work together to polish professional image quality from the bottom up, allowing you to shoot faster, clearer, and better.\r\\n\r\\nThe camera package features Dual-LED dual-tone flash, HDR, and panorama, giving you options depending on the location, lighting and scenery. The primary camera records 4K@30fps, 1080p@30/60/120fps video shots, making the Note 13 Pro worth considering for decent video recording.\r\\n<h3>Processing Power and Efficiency</h3>\r\\nRedmi Note 13 Pro runs on the latest Android 13 OS platform, Android 13, complemented with MIUI 14 for customisation. A <a href=\"https://www.qualcomm.com/products/mobile/snapdragon/smartphones/snapdragon-7-series-mobile-platforms/snapdragon-7s-gen-2-mobile-platform\">Qualcomm SM7435-AB Snapdragon 7s Gen 2 (4 nm)</a> chipset runs operations in the background and ensures efficiency and fast processing of commands. Supporting the chipset and ensuring the seamless running of the handset, whether multi-tasking, live streaming or playing games is the Octa-core (4×2.40 GHz &amp; 4×1.95 GHz) CPU and Adreno 710 GPU. Combined, the processing unit makes a good case regarding reliability, fast processing and enabling prompt response to commands issued by the user without experiencing lags and stuttering.\r\\n\r\\nEqually enabling seamless operations is great RAM and ROM installed on the handset. It has an inbuilt storage space of:\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>128GB 8GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>256GB 8GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>256GB 12GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>512GB 12GB RAM</li>\r\\n 	<li>512GB 16GB RAM</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\nYou can choose from the vast options depending on your preferences and budget. Notably, MicroSD is not supported. However, the ROM is sufficient, offering enough data and multi-media storage space.\r\\n<h3>Network and Communications on Redmi Note 13 Pro</h3>\r\\nRedmi Note 13 Pro’s network connectivity is another great complement that makes it worth owning in 2023. It is 5G enabled and supports up to 5G bands, depending on your network supplier and coverage in your area. With 5G, you are assured of fast uploading and downloading of content and large files. You can opt for the Redmi Note 13 Pro 5G or Redmi Note 13 Pro+ for faster and more efficient uploading and downloading of files, videos and online communication.\r\\n<h3>Sensors on Redmi Note 13 Pro</h3>\r\\nSeveral sensors are installed on the handset, which enables convenience when communicating and handling the device.\r\\n<ul>\r\\n 	<li>Fingerprint (under display, optical)</li>\r\\n 	<li>Accelerometer</li>\r\\n 	<li>gyro</li>\r\\n 	<li>proximity</li>\r\\n 	<li>compass</li>\r\\n</ul>\r\\n<h3>Battery</h3>\r\\nA Li-Po 5,100 mAh, non-removable battery powers the Redmi Note 13 Pro. A fast 67W (PD3.0, 100% in 44 min) charger enabled quick charge of the battery. The new generation battery health management algorithm can learn your daily charging habits, adjust voltage and current in real-time, and delay battery ageing.',NULL,NULL,'Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-13-Pro','Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-13-Pro',21000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(261,'Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 Pro - 256GB','Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 Pro - 256GB','Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-13-Pro-256GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,5,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 Pro - 256GB','Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 Pro',NULL,NULL,'Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-13-Pro-256GB','Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-13-Pro-256GB',42000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL),(262,'Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 Pro - 512GB','Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 Pro - 512GB','Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-13-Pro-512GB','uploads/custom-images/img.png',0,5,0,0,0,20,'200',0,'Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 Pro - 512GB','Xiaomi Redmi Note 13 Pro - 256GB',NULL,NULL,'Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-13-Pro-512GB','Xiaomi-Redmi-Note-13-Pro-512GB',51000,NULL,NULL,0,1,1,1,1,1,1,0,1,NULL,NULL);
